title: butterscotch pecan slices
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the butter and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into two 7-inch rolls and wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or until firm.
Unwrap and cut in 1/4-inch slices.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: happiness is a warm loaf of homemade bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Combine water, milk and margarine in a saucepan; heat over low heat until liquids are warm.
Margarine does not need to melt. Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 3/4 cup of flour to make a thick batter.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff dough (about 3 1/2 cups).
Turn onto floured board and knead until elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk and shape into desired size loaves.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake in hot oven (450°) about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: never fail caramel filling
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring continually. Then add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Cool to lukewarm, then add gradually the powdered sugar and heat. Enough filling for 3 layer cake.

title: summer corn salad
directions: Just before cooking, remove husks and silk from corn; using small vegetable brush, remove any remaining silk.
In large saucepot over medium heat, bring 1 inch of water to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for about 4 to 6 minutes. Drain corn.
When cool enough to handle, use sharp knife to shave kernels from cob into a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir and toss to mix and coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crisco fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, paprika, garlic powder and pepper in a large plastic bag; set aside.
Pour evaporated milk in bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in evaporated milk.
Add a few pieces chicken to bag.
Shake to coat.
Remove chicken from
bag.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Heat Crisco oil in a large skillet.
Add chicken; brown over medium-high heat.
Cook over moderate heat about 25 minutes or until meat near bone is no longer pink and juices run clear, turning pieces over frequently.

title: artichoke-cheese spread
directions: Add mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese to the chopped artichoke hearts.
Put into a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake mixture at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve spread with rye (party) or crackers.
Double recipe for crowd.

title: savory pot roast and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 6- to 8-quart Dutch oven brown meat on both sides in hot oil.
Drain off excess fat.
In a small bowl stir together Marsala wine, 1/3 cup water, basil, garlic salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper; pour over meat.
Cover and bake for 2 hours.

title: ice tea
directions: Place quart jar of water in microwave for 5 minutes.
Remove, place tea bags in hot water and let seep for 5 to 10 minutes. Pour into gallon container removing tea bags and adding sugar. Chill or serve with ice.

title: strawberry shortcake dessert
directions: Lay Twinkies in a deep, flat 2-quart dish.
Mix gelatin as directed on package, minus 1/2 cup water.
Add strawberries with juice to gelatin.
Pour over Twinkies (Twinkies will float). Chill for 1/2 hour to set.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip; garnish with pecans.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and heat until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: savory potato gratin
directions: Saute onions in butter in a large skillet until soft and transparent.
In a shallow baking dish, arrange in layers sliced potatoes and onions, sprinkling with garlic and seasonings in between layers for best flavor.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Add whipping cream all over top.
Increase temperature to 400°.
Bake for another 10 to 20 minutes until potatoes are soft and fork tender and slightly browned on top.
Serve with barbecued meat, chicken or fish.

title: party punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve chilled.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
In a large bowl, mix the hot water and yeast until the yeast dissolves.
Stir in the warm water and the brown sugar.
Slowly add 5 cups of flour to the mixture, stirring constantly.
Continue stirring until the mixture is smooth and does not stick to the sides of the bowl.
Put the dough on a lightly floured board.
Dip your hands in the extra flour.
Knead the dough until it is stretchy and smooth.
Push it down and away from you with the palms of your hands.
Turn the dough as you work.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oleo and 2 eggs with electric mixer.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased and floured.
Batter will be real stiff.
Then beat cream cheese, 2 eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar with mixer and pour on top of batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash squares
directions: Mix well and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes in a large 9 x 13-inch pan or Pyrex dish.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: peanut butter chocolate star cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients. Add flour and soda mixture. Roll into balls and dunk in sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Press stars into cookies and return to oven for 3 minutes more.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and garlic puree until cooked. Set aside.
In double boiler method, combine corn meal, chili powder, milk and tomato juice.
Cook until it gets thick, stirring constantly.
Add corn meal mixture to ground beef.
Add eggs and olives to mixture.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven until crusty on top.

title: simple soda bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and knead the flour.
Bake in oven for 1 hour at 375°.
Let cool before slicing.
Serve with butter or fruit preserves.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, drain well. Cut up vegetables.
Place in pot. Add hamburger, tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce, mushrooms, bay leaf, sugar and water. Bring to boil, then simmer slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until sauce is thick.
Serve over cooked long spaghetti.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: egg rolls
directions: Stew chickens until tender; cool.
Debone and chop into small pieces.
Shred remaining ingredients in food processor (or chop finely).
Mix with chicken.
Stir in soy sauce and 1/4 of the broth from the chicken.
Spoon into middle of egg roll wrappers. Wrap over, tucking in sides.
Secure by moistening edges with water.
Deep fry in oil until lightly browned.
This recipe will serve 12 people.

title: three-bean casserole
directions: To prepare in slow cooker:
Rinse beans in cold water; discard any shriveled beans.
In 3 1/2 to 5-quart slow cooker, cover beans with 6 cups water; let stand at least 12 hours.
Add bacon and remaining ingredients to beans in slow cooker.
Cover; cook on "low" for 12 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candy
directions: Mix sugar and milk and bring to a boil and cook until it makes a soft ball, about 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour in buttered dish.

title: papa's brunswick stew
directions: This recipe is best cooked in a Teflon Chinese wok.
Heat a large pot of boiling water and cook the Penne pasta according to directions.
While the water is boiling, melt unsalted butter in the Teflon wok and brown the garlic.
Once the garlic is browned, place the cooked asparagus and ham in the butter together with the cream.
Raise the heat and boil until the cream is thickened. Turn off the heat and pour cream, asparagus and ham mixture over the Penne.
Mix well and, if desired, add grated cheese to taste.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in 1 cup boiling water.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add soup and milk, simmer 5 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz.
Mix well until Cheez Whiz is melted.
Add broccoli and rice.
Add almonds and seasonings.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: southern homemade biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and mix well.
Turn out on floured board. Roll out and cut.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown.
Yield: 16 to 20 biscuits.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Chop apples; beat eggs slightly.
Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; this will be slightly firm.
Bake in Bundt pan that has been greased well and slightly floured at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let rest for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs and undrained fruit cocktail and mix well.
Turn batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes and remove from pan and place on wire rack.
Place butter, sugar, milk and egg yolk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla to taste, coconut and nuts, mixing well.
Cool icing slightly and spread on top of warm cake.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cool pasta and add broccoli, cauliflower and tomatoes.
Add pepperoni slices and Mozzarella cheese.
Toss lightly with Italian dressing.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: yeast rolls
directions: In a large glass bowl mix yeast and sugar.
Add lukewarm water and stir until yeast is dissolved.
Add salt and cooking oil.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time; mix well.
Turn out on floured cloth. Knead at least 10 minutes.
Put into greased bowl; let rise until double in size.
Turn out on cloth dusted with flour.
Knead for 10 minutes or until smooth.
Make into rolls.
Place on greased cookie sheet or muffin pans.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at about 350° until golden brown.

title: fruit and honey
directions: Mix honey and lemon juice; pour over fruit. Cover and chill until serving time. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Blend in last 4 ingredients.
Mix and heat in a 300° oven until cheese is melted and bubbly (20 minutes).

title: shrimp spread
directions: Crumble shrimp.
Mix ingredients and refrigerate for at least one hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: liver sausage dip
directions: Mix ingredients in electric blender or mixer until smooth. Chill until serving time.

title: crab spread appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds in mixer.
Place in a small casserole dish.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Serve.
Spread on crackers.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and meat until vegetables are just tender. Add next 6 ingredients and dash of pepper.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until thick. Add cheese; stir until melted. Pour onto 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Make Corn Bread Topping.

title: applesauce cake
directions: *Make as you would for the table (sweetened).

title: wedding punch
directions: Bring to boil the sugar and 9 cups water.
Dissolve jello in 6 cups boiling water; add cold water.
Add sugar mixture to jello, then add pineapple juice, lemon juice and almond extract.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Serves 100.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add salt and hot water. Cool.
Add yeast and part of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Gradually add the rest of flour.
Knead until good working dough.
Mix up at 3 p.m.
Knead down at 7 p.m.
About 10 p.m., work down and shape into rolls.
Cover; let set overnight.
Bake at 7 a.m. at 360° for 20 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Cook in heavy pot for 3 minutes on medium heat.
Divide and color each part a different color with few drops of food coloring. Keep in Ziploc bag in refrigerator.

title: soft cutout vanilla cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients and chill for several hours.
Roll out to about 1/8-inch thickness.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will look light in color.
Cool on a rack and decorate with frosting or sprinkle sugar on cookies while warm.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Beat until creamy.
Add milk, vanilla and dry ingredients that are sifted together.
Fold in blueberries that are frozen.
Put into muffin pan liners and fill half full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and cold water and stir until thickened.
Cook mixture for 10 minutes.
Saute onion in shortening.
Add beef and brown.
Stir in flour, olives, tomatoes, chili powder and salt.

title: chocolate coronet
directions: Arrange ladyfingers around side and bottom of 9 inch spring-form pan.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Beat until well blended and smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Blend in chocolate.
Beat egg whites until smooth and stiff and fold in with whipped cream.
Pour into ladyfinger lined spring-form pan. Remove rim of pan.
Garnish with whipped cream and shaved chocolate.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken pieces. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Uncover and bake 1 hour more.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and peanuts in a skillet. Cook over medium-high heat until peanuts pop. Add soda and quickly stir well. Pour onto cookie sheet which has been greased with butter. Smooth with back of spoon. Break into pieces when cool.

title: vegetable bisque with seafood
directions: Combine 2 cups corn and 1 cup broth in a blender; cover and process until smooth.
Set pureed corn aside.
Heat oil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and the next 2 ingredients; saute 5 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in pureed corn mixture, remaining 1 cup broth and milk.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: easy rolls
directions: Place yeast in 2 cups warm water. Melt butter. Cream with sugar in large bowl. Add beaten egg. Add flour. Add yeast and mix well, then refrigerate.
To bake, drop by spoonful into well-greased muffin pans, then bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Dough keeps for several days.

title: raisin (japanese fruit) pie
directions: Cover raisins with water.
Bring to a boil, then drain and cool by running cold water over them.
Let drain while mixing the sugar, margarine (softened), flour, egg (unbeaten) and coconut. Place raisins in unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over raisins and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise in a large bowl.
Add peanuts and mix well.
Add peas; sprinkle with celery seed, salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick pineapple-nut bread
directions: Beat butter gradually, adding sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat until fluffy; stir in Bisquick, salt, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean and top is golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes in pan and turn out on wire rack to cool completely.

title: hearty tomato-beef soup
directions: Saute ground beef, onion and celery in melted butter until meat is well browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Yield:
2 quarts.

title: leek soup
directions: Mix all ingredients, except milk, in a large saucepan and simmer 40 minutes.
Add milk just before serving.
Serve with cornbread.

title: soup burgers
directions: In a skillet brown beef and onions.
Stir in soup and seasonings.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve on buns.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together with spices.
Pour into one pie shell.
Use second shell as top crust.
Seal well and prick for steam vents.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until crust is browned.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Scrape and shred carrots.
Add crushed pineapple, raisins, lemon juice and mayonnaise to moisten (as much or as little as you like).

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 1 1/2-quart baking dish with nonstick spray.
Drain whole kernel corn.
Combine with onions, butter, cream-style corn, sour cream and corn muffin mix in a medium bowl and mix well. Whisk eggs in a small bowl until blended.
Add eggs to corn mixture and mix until all ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into baking dish.
Bake until set, about 45 minutes.

title: acorn squash with cranberry stuffing
directions: Halve acorn squash; scoop out seeds and fibers.
Place squash, cut side down, in baking pan.
Add 1/2-inch water.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
While squash is cooking, melt butter in saucepan. Add salt, lemon or lime juice and apple.
Cook over low heat until apple is tender.
Add cranberries and water.
Cook until cranberries begin to pop.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Turn squash over in pan and fill with cranberry mixture.
Cover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: corn meal chicken liver casserole
directions: Oil an 8 x 10-inch dish.
Cook corn meal according to directions on package.
After completed, pour into 8 x 10-inch dish.
Dice onion.
Fry chicken livers and onion until sauteed. Spoon chicken livers and onion over corn meal with gravy.
Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with hot baked beans and bread and butter.

title: you name it casserole
directions: Brown bacon in very large skillet.
Remove bacon and cool. Add four cups diced potatoes and 1 large onion.
Cook until almost tender.
Shred cabbage and add.
Cook noodles; add.
Continue cooking until everything is tender.
Crumble bacon and spread over top.
We season our own servings with soy sauce.
This is a meal in one skillet.
May have to adjust ingredients to suit your family's taste.

title: oysters mosca
directions: Dip oysters in oil, then in bread crumbs.
Lay in buttered baking dish (no more than 2 to a layer).
Heat butter, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice in saucepan.
Pour over oysters, then top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 minutes.

title: bacon coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl and refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Sift the 1/4 cup of flour with 1 cup of mini chocolate chips and mix. Blend margarine with sugar; add vanilla and cream cheese.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Gradually add the remaining 2 cups of sifted flour and baking powder; mix well, then add the mini chocolate chip mixture and blend.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
After cake is cool, remove from pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hillbilly wine
directions: Thaw juice.
Mix yeast with warm water.
Blend sugar and grape juice.
Combine yeast and grape mixture.
Pour into clean gallon jug and fill jug to within 1 inch of top with water.
Put lid on loose and store in cool, dry place 5 to 6 weeks, then serve. Better if you have stone jug.

title: french beef casserole
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt, pepper and 1 1/2 tablespoons flour. Brown in 2 tablespoons butter and bacon fat.
Place in big casserole.
Put 3 tablespoons flour in skillet with remaining fat and add juices from tomatoes and mushrooms.
Stir until thickens. Pour over meat; add drained tomatoes, cover and bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Take out and add other vegetables, plus instant minced onion, tarragon and basil leaves.
Re-cover and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool; add mushrooms and refrigerate.
To serve, heat oven to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: hot dinner rolls
directions: Mix together yeast, 1 cup flour, sugar and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Melt shortening and add to cooled milk.
Mix with yeast mixture.
Stir well.
Add egg.
Add 1 1/2 cups sifted flour and mix well.
Cover and let rise about 1 1/2 hours.

title: scotch cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, and cinnamon in large bowl.
Mix butter, water, cocoa, and shortening, bring to a boil.
Add flour, mixture, then add milk, eggs one at a time and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Blend until creamy the cream cheese, butter, margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in the flour.
Pour into large greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until light brown.

title: crispy deep fry batter for vegetables
directions: Mix
flour,
salt
and pepper with bottled soda such as ginger ale,
to the consistency of thick pancake batter.	Dip raw vegetables	in
batter
and
fry
in
deep, hot oil. Very crispy! Works well for lobster or fish cubs.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Blend chicken, chilies, onions and soup.
Roll a little of mixture into each tortilla and lay in glass baking dish (don't stack).

title: the snap
directions: Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese; top with shrimp.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread slices.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together real good and then roll them into small balls.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place sausage balls on a greased cookie sheet and bake approximately 30 minutes or until they are done.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender; cool, then debone. Boil celery, onions and bell pepper in broth. Add spaghetti in the broth with veggies until tender, then add soup and deboned chicken. Mix cheese in and put in casserole dish. Bake until lightly brown and bubbly.

title: maple pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Place in flat baking dish.
Combine ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 400°, basting occasionally, 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Remove chops and thicken sauce with flour.

title: pineapple sheath cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Mix.
Add pineapple, oil and dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
(This is thin batter.)
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: hamburger casserole meat loaf
directions: Mix altogether.
Put in pan and make sure macaroni is covered with meat.
Then cover with ketchup.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix all other ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: grater tater casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except cheese).
Pour into large buttered pan.
Cover top with grated cheese.
Dot with butter. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring cranberry sauce to a boil. Add water, then stir in jello. Take off heat. Add pineapple and strawberries. Pour into 9 x 13 glass dish. Refrigerate.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni as directed on the package.
Drain; add butter and cheese.
Cover, let set until butter and cheese melt. Beat the eggs and add milk.
Add this mixture to macaroni.
Pour into buttered dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cake(portuguese)
directions: In an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan, combine the first 5 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Make 3 holes in the mixture. Pour the lemon juice in one hole, the oil in the second and the vanilla in the third.
Pour the cold water over the top and mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hyeholde's cheesecake
directions: Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until foamy. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold egg white mixture into base thoroughly and pour mixture into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until firm.
Turn off oven; open door and leave in oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool on rack away from draft.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Butter 9-inch square pan.
Spread 1/2 cup walnuts evenly on buttered bottom of pan; set aside.
In large saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, sugar, evaporated milk, margarine and salt; bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add butterscotch morsels; stir until morsels melt and mixture is well blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup walnuts on top.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Yield: 2 1/3 pounds.

title: hamburger roll-ups
directions: Combine the hamburger, onion, egg, cheese, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape into patties 1-inch thick.
Place 1 slice of bacon around each patty, securing with a toothpick.
Broil about 5 minutes on each side until done.

title: spicy caesar salad
directions: In food processor, chop garlic and jalapeno to finest consistency possible.
Add next 11 ingredients and blend until of a pureed consistency.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Tear lettuce and pour dressing over.
Toss well and top with croutons.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix well in shaker bottle and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin custard pie(makes 3 to 4 pies)
directions: Use a large bowl.
Beat sugar, cornstarch and margarine well. Add eggs; beat.
Add pumpkin, spices, salt, vanilla and milk. Stir until well blended.
Pour in unbaked pie shells and bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: mom's green tomato relish
directions: Combine the tomatoes, onions, and green peppers.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables and mix well. Boil 25 minutes.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 8+ pints.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix.
Better if it sets for several hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles or rice by directions.
Fix soup being sure to add enough milk or water called for or use 1/2 can of water.
Warm peas; pour some of the juice out.
Pour half of soup in bottom of dish.
Pour rice or noodles on top of soup.
Pour peas over that. Add tuna and other half of soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, soup, Cheddar cheese, sour cream and garlic salt in large bowl; mix well.
Spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Use liquid from peas and enough water to make a can full. Salt and pepper.
Combine all ingredients and simmer until the vegetables are tender.

title: turkey stuffing divan
directions: Mix water and butter. Add stuffing. Mix lightly. Spoon into 2-quart shallow baking dish. Arrange broccoli and turkey over stuffing. In small bowl, mix soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese. Pour over broccoli and turnkey. Sprinkle remaining cheese over soup mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: pepper fingers
directions: Cut end off pepper and hull.
Fill hollow with cheese.
Dip stuffed pepper in onion ring batter and fry like French fries.

title: chicken and zucchini casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Slice unpeeled zucchini crosswise into slices about 1/2-inch thick.
Arrange along bottom of a shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Place chicken over zucchini.
In a small bowl combine remaining ingredients and pour evenly over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Baste chicken with sauce from baking dish and continue cooking for 30 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serves 4.

title: pheasant pot pie
directions: In a large pot combine pheasant, celery, parsley, onion, peppercorns, bay leaf, salt and rosemary.
Add 2 quarts water, bring to a boil.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Remove pheasant, cool and remove meat from bones.
Strain stock.
In 2 cups of stock cook carrots and potatoes about 20 minutes.
In a small bowl mix together milk, flour and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Quickly stir in pot with carrots and potatoes.
Add peas.
Simmer for 8 minutes or until thickened.
Place pheasant pieces in bottom of large casserole.
Pour potato mixture over pheasant.
Cover with pastry. Seal edges around rim of dish.
Cut slash vents in top.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes or until browned.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook noodles as package directs; drain.
Cook onion and green pepper in oleo until tender.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, water chestnuts, pimiento, milk and basil.
Layer half the noodles in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half each of sauce, cottage cheese, chicken, American and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers except for last 2 cheeses.
Reserve cheese for topping. Bake in 350°
oven for 45 minutes.
Top with last 2 cheeses and bake 2 minutes more.
Serves 10.

title: christmas eve sandwiches
directions: Grind raw bacon in meat grinder.
Mix other ingredients in. Spread mixture on hamburger bun halves and broil in oven until bubbly.
One of the many recipes my family enjoys at holiday time.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Bake in small muffin tins at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese meat roll
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt, oregano and pepper; mix well.
Shape into a flat rectangle, about 10 x 12, on waxed paper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over rectangle, roll up like a jelly roll and press ends of roll to seal.
Bake in a shallow baking dish at 350° for 1 hour; drain off fat.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over roll and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: russian chicken
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chicken.
Marinade will be a little lumpy.
Pour over chicken and marinate at least 2 hours.
Cook chicken as is for 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, milk and oleo.
Cook over medium heat until oleo is melted.
Mix cornstarch with milk or water and gradually add to hot mixture.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Stir into fruit.
Top with brown sugar.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add all ingredients to soaked (not soggy) crackers and pour into greased casserole dish.
Dot with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: heath bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil; put about 40 saltine crackers on foil.
Melt brown sugar and margarine.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread as they melt.
Remove from foil (they will stick).
Stack between waxed paper.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy.
Slice apples thin to use with dip.

title: feather biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir yeast into buttermilk; mix well and set aside.
Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk mixture; stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Or cover bowl tightly and store in refrigerator until needed.
(Dough may be stored for up to 3 days.)
Punch dough down; turn dough out on a lightly floured surface.
Knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 3 dozen.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add all other ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Place in airtight covered container and store in refrigerator up to a week.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch square baking pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients until well mixed.
In medium bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup. Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
No fat and no cholesterol.

title: confetti pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.
You can add veggies in any combination; use your imagination!
Add cooked chicken or ham if using as main dish!

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; beat until light and fluffy. Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time. Mixture should look like pale-yellow whipped cream. Add dry ingredients and vanilla to mixture. Put bowl of cookie dough into refrigerator. Chill at least 2 hours. Set oven at 375°; bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are a nice light brown color.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix well and put on top of chicken.
Bake at 375 ° for 20 minutes (or longer if it has been refrigerated before baking) until bubbly and hot.
Serves 4.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: All vegetables to partially defrost at room temperature.
Mix soup and sour cream; stir into vegetables.
Mix 1/2 of onions and 1/2 of cheese into mixture.
Microwave, covered, on High for 8 minutes.
Garnish with rest of onions and cheese.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 1 minute.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Melt butter. Add chicken and Cajun spice. Add all other seasonings.
Mix. Add onions, stirring often. Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes. Warm cream and simmer 2 minutes. Add after warming, then simmer for 20 minutes. Add pasta on top and toss lightly or serve separately.

title: shrimp linguini
directions: In a large frying pan, saute oil, margarine and garlic.
Clean shrimp (in advance) and place around edge of pan.
Add white wine. Crush plum tomatoes with fork and add to pan.
Sprinkle spices over mixture and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour over linguini.

title: skillet beans and squash
directions: Heat all ingredients except cilantro to boiling in 10-inch skillet sprayed with Pam cooking spray.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until vegetables are tender (approximately 7 minutes). Stir in cilantro.
Serves 4.
Contains 100 calories, 1 gram fat and 0 milligrams cholesterol.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar and baking soda.
Add vinegar, flour and nuts.
Blend well.
Drop with teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
4 to 4 1/2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add to squash and stir.
Add soup, cheese and 1 cup crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into baking dish and top with 1/2 cup crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream
directions: Place
in blender all ingredients.
Blend 30 seconds or until the mixture is creamy.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and pour in casserole dish. Chill for several hours.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream margarine and Fruit Sweet.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend in lemon juice and yogurt.
Stir in lemon peel and chopped pulp. In separate bowl combine flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and wheat germ.
Add to batter.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan which has been sprayed with nonstick coating.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 16 slices.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and boil 10 minutes or more.
Add cream of chicken soup, the one pound of cheese which has been cubed and the mushrooms.
Stir over heat until well blended.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: sarah's quick start breakfast drink
directions: Mix in blender until smooth.

title: date bar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: ten-layer casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a 1 3/4-quart deep sided baking dish or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
In small bowl, combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, relish, garlic powder and dry mustard.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 of the rice in the prepared baking dish.
Top with 1/2 the corn, spoon 1/2 of the kidney beans evenly over the corn.
Top with 1/2 onions and 1/2 sauce. Top with remaining rice, then corn, beans, onions and remaining sauce.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: rich cocoa brownies
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add sugar, butter and vanilla. Add cocoa, flour and salt. Beat until smooth. Line a 9-inch square pan with parchment paper. Spray parchment paper with Pam. Pour brownie batter onto parchment. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes or until done. Toothpick comes out clean. Onto a cooling rack, lift parchment paper out of pan to rack. Pull paper away from brownies. When cool, cut with a pizza cutter. Delicious and so rich! Serves 1 to 2 chocoholics. Can freeze.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix sherbet in milk, reserving some for top.
Add Squirt or 7-UP and orange juice.
Make 10 minutes before serving.
Top with reserved sherbet.
Makes 32 punch servings.

title: pork with sauerkraut
directions: Cover the spareribs with cold water; bring to a boil.
Skim the fat.
Add all ingredients, except barley.
Simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours, or until the meat is tender.
Add barley 20 minutes before meat is done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate cheese and mix with sausage and Bisquick.
Form small balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on broiler pan and bake 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fluffy peach delight
directions: Place cracker crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Melt Jell-O in 2 cups of hot water.
Stir in cream cheese and marshmallows until melted.
Let mixture cool.
Add peaches and 1 tub of Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and refrigerate until set. When completely set, top with second container of Cool Whip.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: new york meatballs
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, mushrooms and tomatoes in skillet for 30 minutes.
Then add all ingredients, along with hamburger patties to which you have added salt, pepper and garlic salt. Cook on very low heat 1 hour.
I serve this with spaghetti and we have meatball sandwiches on French bread.

title: puree of onion soup with thyme leaves
directions: Saute butter, potatoes and onions until well coated with butter.
Add thyme, rosemary and paprika.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 10 minutes until potatoes and onions are soft, but browned.
Add chicken stock and bring to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Puree in blender or food processor to make smooth.
Serve in soup bowls garnished with a sprinkling of thyme leaves.

title: lemony cheesecake squares(makes 12 to 15 servings.)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 8 minutes. Cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Add eggs and ReaLemon brand; mix well.
Spread preserves evenly over prepared crust.
Pour cheese mixture over preserves. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fresh peach sauce with grand marnier
directions: In a microwave container, combine 1/4 cup water with sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 2 to 4 minutes or until boiling rapidly.
Stir in peaches and Grand Marnier. Chill.
Serve over ice cream.
Serves 4.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Boil ingredients together all but the cucumbers.
When boiling, add cucumbers.
Boil everything, then put in heated jars and seal.

title: czechoslovakian squares
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolk, flour and nuts.
Spread half of this mixture in ungreased square pan. Spread with jam.
Top with remaining cake mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Cut in squares.

title: cheesecake - my way
directions: Beat together sugar and cream cheese.
Whip milk.
Add chilled jello to cheese mixture, beating slowly.
Fold in milk to mixture with spoon or hand whip.
Pour into dish and chill 1 1/2 hours. Spoon cherry pie filling over cake and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Chill 1/2 hour more before serving.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel the apples and put them in a bowl.
Then you cook it and you smash.
Then you put cinnamon.
Then you eat it.

title: wild rice
directions: Boil wild rice 50 minutes (keep covered with water).
While rice is boiling, saute onions and mushrooms in 1 stick of butter. Season with Lawry's seasoned salt and seasoned pepper.
When rice is cooked, rinse in hot water and drain.
Add rice to mushrooms and onions.
Add second stick of butter.
Heat until butter is melted and rice mixture is warm.

title: toast cups
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Butter one side of each slice.
Press buttered side down in muffin cups.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 12 minutes or until lightly toasted.
You can then fill these to make individual servings of any egg, cheese or meat dish.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Put oranges in basket of 30 cup percolator.
Mix spices together and sprinkle over oranges.
Put cider in percolator and percolate as for coffee.

title: fried rice cakes
directions: In a bowl, combine eggs, rice, bacon, green pepper, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and chill at least one hour.
Using 1/3 cup rice mixture for each, shape in patties about 3 1/2-inches in diameter.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine
until onions are wilted. Blend flour in well with this mixture.
Pour in the milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, salt, red and black pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Put crabmeat in mixing bowl and pour the cooked sauce over the crabmeat.
Blend well and then transfer into a lightly greased casserole and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Serves 6.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Press ground beef into bottom of 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with milk, salt and
pepper.
Layer potatoes, onions, soup and cheese on top. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots 10 minutes after they start to boil.
They should be firm.
Combine all ingredients and pour over carrots.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: lemon chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine egg, milk, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken breasts in this mixture and then in bread crumbs.
Heat olive oil in skillet; saute chicken very quickly, just until browned.
Put in flat Pyrex casserole.
Pour the chicken broth over it.
Sprinkle with white wine, then with Parmesan cheese and lastly the lemon juice.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes, then uncover and cook 10 minutes more.

title: homemade pizza sauce
directions: Cook
tomatoes, onions, garlic and fresh parsley.
Then run through ricer.
Return to kettle and add remaining ingredients. Cook
to
desired thickness, about 4 hours.
Good for spaghetti too.

title: dorothy's fermented pickles
directions: Bring to a boil and pour this mixture into jar.
Then fill the jar with boiling water.
Do not use for 10 days.
After 10 days, place in refrigerator and serve.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until clear. Cool slightly.
Beat the egg whites until frothy. Continue beating while slowly pouring cooked mixture in.
Beat 5 minutes. Cover cooled pie, sealing edges to crust. Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: vegetable barley soup
directions: Brown meat and drain; stir in rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer until vegetables are tender. Additional water may be added if soup becomes too thick. Serves 8 to 10 cups.

title: chili-beer brisket
directions: Place meat in a roasting pan, fat side up. Put the chopped vegetables over the meat; pour the chili sauce and water over all. Cover and bake at 325° for 3 or 3 1/2 hours. Let cool 20 minutes. Slice thin and pour the beer over the brisket. Place back in the oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan, over low heat, for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
In separate bowl, combine melted chocolate mixture, 1 cup flour, sugar, eggs, baking powder and salt.
Beat until well mixed, 2 to 3 minutes.
By hand, stir in remaining flour and nuts.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, 2 hours or overnight.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to the directions on the package.
After cake is cooked, punch holes in it and pour the milk and caramel over it.
Let cake cool.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crushed Heath bar candy over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
This cake is best if made several hours before serving.

title: black forest cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Mix and press first 2 ingredients into spring-form pan.
Refrigerate until batter is ready.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Crush 1 package crackers and sprinkle over this, and dot with 1/2 stick butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: buttercrust flake-aparts
directions: These light tender rolls separate easily into bite-sized pieces.
They look fancy, but are easily made.

title: pumpkin bran muffins
directions: Spray 12 muffin cups with a nonfat cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In a
large bowl, using a wire whisk, beat Egg Beaters. Stir in pumpkin, cereal, milk and corn syrup.
Add to flour mixture. Stir until well blended.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool in pan 5 minutes. Yields 12 muffins.

title: egg salad
directions: Hard-boil eggs and chop.
Chop olives.
Finely chop onion. Combine all ingredients and spread on buttered bread.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: boil cookies
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cocoa, oleo and milk.
Bring to a boil, to a full rolling boil.
Take off stove; add oats and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: gazpacho
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Puree in a blender, 1/2 at a time, with enough of the tomato juice to cover.
Put puree in a bowl.
Beat in oil, vinegar, remaining tomato juice, salt, pepper and Tabasco. Chill.

title: warm corn salad
directions: In a medium pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion; cook stirring occasionally until very tender, about 10 minutes. Stir in corn, cumin, lime zest and juice, salt and pimentos. Cover and cook until heated through, about 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: microwave macaroni cheese deluxe
directions: Place the macaroni in large bowl with the water and salt.
Cook in microwave for 15 minutes. Stir twice during cooking.
Drain and rinse.
Melt the butter in a bowl for 1 minute, then add the onion and continue cooking for 6 minutes.
Stir in the flour to absorb the butter, then gradually mix in the milk.
Add the grated cheese and cook in the microwave for 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Add the macaroni, season lightly and return to the microwave for 4 minutes, stirring 4 times during cooking.

title: pineapple icebox pudding
directions: Mix pineapple (juice and all), pecans, eggs and sugar.
Add butter by slicing into small pieces.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients and cover.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Slice peaches.
Pour sugar and lemon juice over peaches.
Let stand one hour.
Drain.
Should be one cup.
If not, add enough water to make 1 cup.
Cook liquid with cornstarch and salt until thickened, then cool.
Add coloring and almond extract.
Cool completely.
Add to peaches.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mixed bean casserole
directions: Lightly brown bacon and onion in large skillet.
Remove from heat.
Stir in all beans, cheese, brown sugar, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Ladle into shallow baking dish.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: cranberry delight salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar; mix well.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple with its juice and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
Let thaw 5 minutes before serving.

title: nutmeg feather cake
directions: Cream 1/4 cup margarine and 1/4 cup shortening with sugar.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add alternately with 1 cup buttermilk, 2 cups flour, nutmeg, soda, baking powder and salt. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat well, then add pumpkin and water.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add to pumpkin mixture. Fold in nuts and raisins.
Grease (or spray with Pam) and flour 2 large loaf pans or 3 small pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bacon and chives potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cook bacon crisp.
Mix mayonnaise and dijon mustard.
Cut up green onion.
Toss all together.

title: carrot-cheese casserole
directions: Cook carrots until barely tender.
In a saucepan, melt butter; add next 7 ingredients.
Cook until thick.

title: lasagna
directions: In a skillet, cook the ground beef and onion until the meat is done.
Do not drain the meat.
Pour meat and onions in large bowl.
Add all the remaining ingredients to the meat and onions, except the noodles and parmesan cheese.

title: norman's meat loaf
directions: Put dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs and milk, mixing together.
Form oblong loaf and place in baking dish.
Brown top under broiler for a few minutes.
Bake with lid for 1 hour at 300°, then remove lid and bake for 20 to 25 minutes or microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or to temperature of 160° to 170°.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage into skillet.
Brown and drain.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls firmly pressed to seal.
Sprinkle the sausage and cheese onto the rolls. Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour over the sausage and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until set.
Let it stand for 5 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: unbelievable lasagna
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread about 1 cup sauce.
Arrange a layer of uncooked noodles.
Top with sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan and sauce.
Repeat, gently pressing the lasagna pieces into the cheese mixture below.
End with a final layer of lasagna pieces.
Pour remaining sauce over the top, making sure all pieces are covered with sauce.
Top with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Do not be concerned about the empty spaces at the end of the pan.
The lasagna will expand during cooking.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes until lightly browned and bubbly.
Allow to stand 15 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: blueberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 2 cups juice; chill until partially set.
Add well drained fruits; mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate at least overnight.
On the day this is to be served, prepare topping. (Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.)
Spread on top of gelatin; sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: whole wheat oatmeal cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Stir together whole wheat flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, walnuts and raisins.

title: cranberry fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cranberries and cream in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to medium.
Cook for four minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in vanilla chips and melt, which should be about one minute longer.
Remove from heat and stir in Marshmallow Creme and pecans.
Pour onto a well buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool at room temperature, then refrigerate.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Grate zucchini.
Cream the margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add zucchini.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Crush cranberries, pineapple and sugar in a blender and put boiling water over jello; add 1 cup cold water and mix.
Put in bowl and freeze until using.

title: rose's fried rice
directions: First Cooking Pan:
Melt 1/4 stick margarine.
Mix raw eggs with salt, pepper and milk.
Scramble eggs until done.
Set this pan to the side.

title: broiled french tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in half cutting across the grain.
Arrange on a baking sheet.
Add salt and pepper. Mix the garlic,
oil and bread crumbs together and place some on the open face of each tomato half.
Sprinkle a bit of basil on each and top with about 1 tsp. cheese for each tomato.
Broil until cheese melts a bit and turns golden brown.
Remove from oven and heat oven to 375°.
Heat the tomatoes for about 15 minutes before serving.
Do not overcook or they will be mushy.

title: hot chile sauce
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes and cut in pieces.
After boiling tomatoes for 2 hours, add onions and peppers and add cinnamon, ginger, cloves, dry mustard and sugar.
Boil for 1/2 hour and then add
1/2 pint vinegar.
Boil 1/2 hour more, put into hot canning jars and seal.

title: wilton cake decorating icing
directions: Cream Crisco and butter; add sugar, milk or water and vanilla. Blend on medium speed until well mixed.
To make chocolate, add 1/4 cup cocoa and 1 tablespoon or more of milk or water.

title: mango ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in a ice cream maker or in the freezer.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind first 8 ingredients and blend together.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Boil until hot and add to ground garden vegetables and boil 15 or 20 minutes.
Put into quart jars and seal.

title: herbed cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: tea biscuits(makes 12 biscuits)
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in lukewarm water.
Add melted shortening and half of flour.
Beat well until smooth.
Add salt and balance of flour (or at least enough to make a moderately firm dough).
Knead thoroughly.
Roll and cut with biscuit cutter. Place on well-greased pan a slight distance apart.
Cover and let rise (about 2 hours).
Bake in 425° oven for 10 minutes.

title: brandy slush
directions: Steeped tea must sit for 1/2 hour.
Simmer together water, orange juice, sugar and lemonade until sugar melts in simmer pot. After tea is steeped, add to simmer pot.
When cool, add 2 cups of brandy.
Stir well.
Put into Tupperware and freeze.
Stir a couple of times before it freezes hard, about 12 hours.
Will last for about a year in the freezer.
Fill a glass with slush, then add Sprite to the top of the glass.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients (except nuts) in double boiler.
Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix. Spread candy quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: orange balls
directions: Cream margarine and add sugar; mix well.
Blend in orange juice, then vanilla wafer crumbs.
Pinch off small pieces and form into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Refrigerate until firm.
Makes approximately 6 dozen balls.

title: split pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot or large pan.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 to 12 hours.
(Crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours.) Add water, if needed.
Start with less water when using crock-pot.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix bananas and pineapple together so all bananas are coated with pineapple.
Mix all the other ingredients together and freeze.
Thaw until slushy; eat with a spoon.

title: pork casserole #1
directions: Saute the meat in the oil.
Add the chopped vegetables.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add the soup, mushrooms with liquid and the seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix noodles with the meat sauce and spread in a buttered 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Mix the bread crumbs with melted butter and grated cheese and spread over the top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: almond cookies
directions: *To toast almonds, bake in ungreased shallow pan in 350° oven 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until golden brown.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Combine butter, shortening and sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in vanilla and food coloring.
Combine salt and flour, add to cream mixture alternatively with milk, bearing well.
Pour batter into a greased, floured 10 inch tube pan.
Bake at 325 degrees about 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cook cake completely.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: pioneer sugar cookies
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream together butter, shortening, Pioneer sugar and vanilla.
Add egg.
Mix until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass which has been dipped in Pioneer sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Yield:
5 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: cheese and carrot sandwiches
directions: In medium bowl, toss together grated carrots and cheese. Divide and spread mayonnaise evenly among bread slices.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spread 8 slices with carrot-cheese mixture. Top with remaining bread slices.
Trim off crusts and cut each sandwich into 4 squares, triangles, or fingers.

title: taco pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle corn meal in pan.
Wet fingers and pat Bisquick dough into pan. If using refried beans, spread beans on.
Brown ground beef.
Add water and seasoning according to directions on back of taco mix. Add onion, tomatoes and green chili.
Spread beef mixture over beans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400°.
Cut into large, cake-size pieces.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
well, then bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Can be baked in two round cake pans or one (9 x 13-inch) pan or 12 x 18-inch pan.

title: cherry berries on a cloud
directions: Bake Meringue Shells.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in chilled bowl.
Beat cream until stiff.
Gently fold whipped cream and the marshmallows into cream cheese mixture.
Pile into shells. Cover; chill at least 12 hours.
Just before serving, top with cherry pie filling, which is mixed with 1 teaspoon lemon juice. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for almonds.
Sprinkle almonds over mixture; spread onto oblong baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika over almonds.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Boil chicken and tear into pieces. Prepare stuffing mix. Stir in melted butter. Put half of stuffing mix in a large casserole dish. Mix chicken soup, broth and milk. Layer chicken on top of stuffing. Pour mixture over top of chicken. Add the rest of the stuffing on top and bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in a tightly closed container.
For 1 cup of tea, mix 2 heaping teaspoons of mixture in 1 cup hot water.

title: cinnamon swirl cake
directions: Beat all ingredients, except sugar and cinnamon, well with mixer.
Blend sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top of batter and cut with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a well-greased Bundt pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: On medium heat, melt butter, milk, peanut butter, cocoa and sugar.
When it begins to boil, cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well and spoon onto wax paper.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix and press in 8 x 8-inch pan chopped pecans, oleo and flour.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Blend Cool Whip, powdered sugar, cream cheese and milk with instant chocolate pudding until thick and spread on cooled pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip and grated Hershey bar or grated pecans or both!

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water until tender. Save broth. Skin and debone chicken breasts and shred or just tear into small pieces. Cook rice using 2 cups of chicken broth instead of water. When rice is done, add soup, sour cream, shredded chicken and 1 cup of broth. Mix well. Put into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and put grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: cherry pink muffins
directions: Line muffin wells with pink and white paper cups.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir to blend and make a well in center.
Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Finely chop and measure cherries (should be about 3/4 cup).

title: cajun crawfish etouffee
directions: Over medium heat, slowly melt butter and tomato paste.
Combine onions, bell pepper and celery and cook until onions are tender. Add crawfish.
Blend cornstarch with cold water to form a smooth paste and stir into crawfish mixture.
Season with Cajun seasoning or with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 15 minutes over medium heat, stirring often.
Serve over rice, garnished with a parsley sprig.
Yields 4 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter, then add liquids.
Mix until just moistened.
Spread peaches in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with dough.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: diane's fruit salad
directions: GENTLY combine all fruits in large bowl & toss
Squeeze juice from grapefruit rind over fruit.

title: "heavenly" french toast
directions: Melt butter; pour 1/2 amount in baking dish that was sprayed with Pam.
Beat eggs; combine with milk and sugar.
Cut bread into 2-inch slices; dip in milk and egg mixture and place in baking dish.
Pour remaining milk and eggs on top of bread to completely soak.
Pour rest of butter on top.
Bake at 400° until golden brown; turn once if necessary.
Remove from oven and sprinkle heavily with powdered sugar, sparingly with cinnamon.

title: chili for a crowd
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, celery and green peppers.
Cook for about 5 minutes and add tomatoes.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Add chili powder and stir.
Add tomato sauce and sugar.
Cook slowly for about 1 1/2 hours, stirring fairly frequently to prevent sticking.
Serves about 20 hungry people.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Layer ingredients in rice cooker as listed.
When rice cooker alarms, let stand on warm for about 15 minutes.
Stir well.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll thick.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 8 minutes. Put in cookie jar while still warm.

title: linguine with cream cheese
directions: Mix tomatoes, cream cheese, oil, basil, vinegar, salt and pepper in large bowl. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Cook pasta as directed on package. Drain. Place in large bowl. Add tomato mixture and pine nuts. Toss lightly and serve. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Mix with your hands; shape into a ball.
Chill.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: In 1-quart casserole, blend together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk, mixing well.
Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes. Stir every 3 minutes until mixture is smooth, thickened and clear.
Stir small amount of hot pudding into egg yolks. Return egg mixture to hot pudding, mixing well.
Microwave 1 to 3 minutes. Add butter and vanilla. Stir. Add rice to pudding. Stir and serve.
(Raisins may be added.)

title: pancake syrup
directions: In 2 quart glass
casserole
boil
water
(about
2 1/2 minutes).
Add brown sugar and heat 2 to 3 minutes until sugar is dissolved,
stirring
frequently as mixture boils.
Stir in flavoring.
Makes 2 cups.

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs. Layer on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with pineapple and juice in a saucepan.
Heat until Jell-O dissolves.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts. Place in large Pyrex bowl.
Top with sprinkle of nuts.

title: red beans with rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in water.
Drain in morning.
Cook beans and ham in water for 1 hour.
Then add all ingredients except seasoned salt.
Cook another 1 1/2 hours.
Cook 1 hour.
Reheat, simmer 1 hour and add seasoned salt to taste.
Serve over cooked rice.
Great with cornbread.
Serves 8.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: *Made with 1 cup 1% low-fat cottage cheese, blended with 2 tablespoons of plain nonfat yogurt and 2 tablespoons of lemon juice in blender until smooth.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add orange juice. Stir well.
Drain both mandarin orange slices and crushed pineapple.
Add to jello mixture. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill well.

title: dump brownies
directions: Dump all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Using an electric mixer, mix until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In large skillet melt butter and brown meat and mushrooms; remove from skillet.
Into drippings in the skillet stir flour and onion soup mix; gradually add water and reserved liquid.
Return meat and mushrooms to pan.
Simmer covered for 10 minutes.
Blend in sour cream and heat through.
Serve over noodle.s

title: aunt thelms's perking roast beef
directions: Take a large knife and cut slits in the roast insert slices of garlic and onion. You can use only onion if you wish. Put the beef in a bowl and pour 1 c. of vinegar over it, making sure the vinegar runs down into the slits in the beef. Place in the refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours. When ready to cook the roast, pour the vinegar off and place the meat in a heavy pot (a cast iron if possible). Brown in oil until very dark on both sides. Pour 2 c. of coffee over the roast, add 2 c. water and cover. Cook slowly for 6 hours on top of stove. If your roast is cooked to fast or if your lid on your pot is not tight enough you may need to add more water. Never add more than 1 c. at a time. Do not season with anything else until 20 minutes before serving then salt and pepper.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop tablespoons of dough on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake one sheet at a time at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool 2 minutes before removing from sheet.

title: rosemary cheese fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Place remaining ingredients in a bowl and mix in the melted butter. Press mixture in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into finger size pieces.

title: sweet and sour cashew chicken
directions: Reserving 1/3 cup syrup, drain peaches.
Cut slices in half. Blend reserved syrup and sweet and sour sauce; set aside.
Cut chicken into 1-inch square pieces.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, ginger and sugar.
Stir in chicken.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in hot wok or large skillet over high heat.
Add chicken and stir-fry 4 minutes.
Remove.
Heat remaining oil in same pan.
Add onion, green pepper and carrot; stir-fry 4 minutes.
Stir in chicken and sweet and sour sauce mixture.
Cook, stirring until chicken and vegetables are coated with sauce.
Stir in peaches and cashews; heat through.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Blend together and enjoy.

title: crispy herbed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Grease a 15 x 10 or 13 x 9-inch pan. In a bowl, combine potato flakes, cheese, parsley, onion, garlic, salt, paprika and pepper. Stir. Dip chicken in melted margarine and roll in potato flakes mixture to coat.
Put in pan and bake at 375° for 60 to 75 minutes or until done.

title: deviled shrimp
directions: Clean raw
shrimp and chop coarsely.
Saute onion until clear in	melted	butter.
Add
mustard, seasoning, shrimp and flour, stirring
constantly.
Add	milk and cook until mixture boils, stirring
constantly.
Remove from heat and add sherry. Pour into casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 for cocktails or 4 as a main dish.

title: rock buns(cookies)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and butter like you would a pie crust.
Mix milk and egg together and add to mixture. Add flavoring.
Dough should be stiff.
Add raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes (check; cookies may only need 11 minutes).
Cool and ice.

title: aunt neoma's hot rolls
directions: On top of stove, cook over medium heat the milk, margarine, Crisco, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Do not boil; cook just long enough to melt margarine and Crisco.
While this is cooling, mix together the yeast, 1 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar.
Set this aside.
After cooked ingredients have cooled, add yeast mixture and enough flour to make a stiff dough (about 7 cups).
Before dough gets real stiff, add 3 eggs.
Put in warm place; let rise.
After dough has risen, place on floured surface and work in enough flour so dough is not sticky.
Roll out dough; cut with biscuit cutter or glass and place into greased pan.
Let rise again, then bake at 350° until brown.

title: "cherry angel"
directions: Break angel food cake into 1-inch pieces and place in bottom of pie plate or 8 x 8-inch serving dish.
Mix pudding with milk and sour cream, then pour over cake.
Spread pie filling on top. Chill.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter.
In separate bowl, combine sugars, Karo and cream.
Add mixture to butter and bring to a boil.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes, stirring rapidly.
Add 2 squares of melted chocolate and boil 5 minutes rapidly at first and more slowly toward the end. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Add walnuts. When nearly cool, cut into squares.

title: chicken with dried chestnuts
directions: Soak dried chestnuts in several changes of water for 16 to 24 hours.
Mix chicken, light soy, sherry, ginger, onions, salt and white pepper.
Allow to marinate for 30 to 45 minutes.
Drain and save the marinade.
Soak mushrooms in hot water for 1 hour.
Brown chicken in oil, a few at a time, so that they brown rather than stew.
Put chicken, soaked chestnuts, marinade, stock and mushrooms in a stove top casserole.
Cover and simmer until chestnuts are tender.
Thicken with cornstarch and water mixture.
Garnish with sesame oil and chopped onions.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Bring salt, pepper, sugar, oil, vinegar and water to a boil and dissolve good.
Pour this over drained vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and serve.
Will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: martha's company casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Spread 1/2 in a 2-quart casserole.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
Spread over noodles and cover with remaining noodles.
Pour melted butter over noodles.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Blend banana and 1/2 of the pineapple juice.
Mix into syrup.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into plastic container.
Cool and serve.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place bacon in large skillet, add margarine and saute for several minutes.
Add all other ingredients except for shrimp, simmer for 10 minutes.
Place shrimp in open baking dish and pour sauce over top.
Stir once to coat all shrimp.
Bake in uncovered dish for 20 minutes, stirring several times during process.
Serve hot.
Eat at once.

title: sunday baked ham
directions: Place ham on rack in roasting pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Trim excess fat and rind with a sharp knife.
Score fat in a diamond pattern; insert cloves where points meet.
In a small saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, orange juice, brown sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Brush glaze on ham.
Return to oven.
Bake 1 hour, brushing with glaze every 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry.
Remove stems. Chop stems and combine with sausage, garlic and parsley.
Cook until sausage is brown (in skillet on top of stove), stirring to crumble.
Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in cheese, mixing well.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; skin and debone.
Cut into pieces and set aside. Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
You may need to add more water. In a boiler, melt Velveeta, Ro-Tel and soups.
Add chicken to spaghetti.
Pour cheese mixture over all.
Mix well.

title: banana blueberry pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Fold in whip topping bananas.
Pour into pie shells and spread pie filling on top.
refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Just before serving, garnish with blueberries and slice bananas, and mint if desired.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press crescent rolls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, dressing and sour cream until smooth.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Place broccoli, cauliflower, peppers and onions on top (fresh veggies work best). Top with cheese.
Chill.

title: frosty sherbet punch
directions: Have juices and ginger ale thoroughly chilled.
Empty one can of each juice and one quart ginger ale into punch bowl.
Add a quart of sherbet.
Spoon the liquid over the sherbet until partly melted.
Serve.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Marinate 2 pounds of round steak/roast, cut 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick, for at least 3 days. Cook on grill or broil in the oven.

title: joe's taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large salad bowl.
Add dressing just before serving.
Makes a meal in itself!

title: one egg cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add melted butter and 1/2 cup of milk to make paste and add egg.
Mix well, then add the rest of the milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Good with strawberries and whipped cream or plain.

title: chicken and artichokes
directions: Place chicken and artichokes in greased 14 x 11 x 3-inch baking dish.
Combine margarine, flour, cheese, nutmeg and broth in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, until cheese is melted and sauce is thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken and artichokes.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs, savory and thyme on sauce and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil; add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with zucchini.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Bake in Bundt pan.
Add dates or nuts, if desired.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat soda into hot applesauce; stir and thoroughly mix with sugar and shortening.
Add spices, nuts, fruit and flour in order given.
This should be very thick and heavy batter.
If mixture is too thin, just add more flour. Grease and flour pan or baking dish.
Bake slow at 250°.

title: jason's cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Accent and onion until well combined. Form into ball and roll in beef. Serve with crackers.

title: hot or cold tea
directions: Put tea bags into 2 quarts of boiling water.
Let it steep 10 minutes.
Make a syrup of sugar and 1 cup water; pour into gallon jug.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Add tea to mixture.
Let cool and pour into jug; fill with water to the top.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir it thoroughly.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly, and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seed and beat for a few minutes.
Store in refrigerator, but not near the freezing coil. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: dollies
directions: Melt oleo in long pan and press crumbs into oleo. Layer the chips, coconut and nuts on top of this. Pour Eagle Brand condensed milk over this and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies with pudding
directions: Mix soda and flour.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture then stir in chips, oats and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.) Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: corn flake cookie
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and baking powder. Cream shortening and sugars together. Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients. Add coconut and corn flakes. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 8 dozen.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt or angel food pan.
Cream margarine and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix flour and baking soda. Alternate dry ingredients and sour cream, making 3 additions of dry and 2 of sour cream.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except water in large bowl.
Add boiling water and stir well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool. Dust with powdered sugar or frost with butter frosting.

title: granny's rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients, except raisins, in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours, then stir in raisins and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookie pie
directions: Microwave marshmallows and 2 tablespoons of milk in medium bowl on High for 45 seconds.
Stir (marshmallows will be partially melted).
Refrigerate 15 minutes to cool.
Stir in 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Pour 2 cups of milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute or until thickened.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Arrange cookies over pudding mixture.
Spread marshmallow mixture over cookies.

title: philly fondue
directions: Pour milk into fondue pot; heat until scalded.
Add cream cheese; cook at low heat, stirring, until cream cheese is melted. Add mustard, onions and dried beef.
Cook, stirring, for 5 minutes longer.
Serve with French bread cubes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, salt, butter and syrup.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes of until done.
Cool before serving.

title: raspberry champagne punch
directions: In blender container, puree raspberries.
In large punch bowl, combine pureed raspberries, lemon juice, sugar and wine.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, scoop sherbet into punch bowl; add Asti Spumante.
Stir gently.

title: school soup
directions: Put beef in 2 quarts warm water and stir well to separate beef.
Salt to taste.
Boil on medium heat until beef is well done.
Add potatoes, onion, carrots and peas.
