Stir occasionally to keep beef separated.
Add tomato paste and simmer 15 minutes. Serve with toasted cheese sandwiches, cheese toast, cornbread or crackers.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: In wok	or
skillet,
saute shrimp and pork with garlic and small amount of Accent.
Drain and place in bowl.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meatball ingredients together (hamburg, egg, garlic powder, bread crumbs and duck sauce).
Roll and bake at 350° until done. Put grape jelly and chili sauce together.
Cook on stove until boiling.
Put meatballs in sauce and cook on slow for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake according to directions.
Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip, Ranch dressing, dill weed and garlic; spread on crescent crust.
Spread chopped veggies on top.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
A Salad Shooter works well for chopping.

title: casserole italiano
directions: In a skillet, brown beef with onion, garlic and seasonings. Stir to separate meat.
Combine in 1 1/2-quart casserole with soup, water and noodles.
Place cheese around edge and atop of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa and milk.

title: cheesy mushroom chicken
directions: Place chicken in deep dish with a little water to cover.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Pour in soup, water and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, pour cheeses over chicken and bake in oven 15 minutes longer.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish, add hash browns, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and 1 cup cheese.
Mix well.
Add remaining cheese on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake it just as you would regular corn bread.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Saute onion until clear.
Combine egg and milk; add biscuit mix.
Stir until moist.
Add onion, parsley and 1/2 cheese.
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and butter. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in 1/4-inch pieces.
Put in bowl and mix with cornstarch.
Add slightly beaten egg and sugar; mix well.
Turn into unbaked crust.
Cut butter pieces and put on rhubarb mixture. Cover with top crust.
Brush top crust with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Cut slits in crust and bake at 425° for 30 minutes, then at 325° for another 30 minutes.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix and put in casserole dish. Top with margarine, salt and pepper. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes (until brown on top).

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients and mix well.
Cover and chill about 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with tines of fork dipped in sugar to form crisscross pattern.
Bake for 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Cool completely and store tightly covered.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: breckenridge soup(broccoli)
directions: Saute butter, onion, carrot and broccoli.
Add cream of chicken soup and milk.
Cook on low until vegetables are tender and blended in 30 to 40 minutes.
Tastes just as good reheated.

title: cheezy chicken
directions: Place cut up chicken in cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Salt and pepper.
Place cheese over all.
Mix soups and pour over chicken, then sprinkle with rice.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours or until chicken is done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place sliced apples into pie dish.
Sprinkle lemon juice on top.
Mix all remaining ingredients until crumbly, not oily. Spread this mixture over apples.
Bake in pie pan for 30 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: apple caramel cake
directions: Put everything but last 2 ingredients into bowl in order given.
Add boiling water and beat batter just until smooth with an electric mixer (or egg beater) on half speed.
Stir in apples that are not peeled but have been quartered and chopped.
Pour into 2 greased, round cake pans and bake in moderate oven at 375° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: chewy caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13 pan on bottom and sides with margarine or Crisco.
Measure all ingredients into a large bowl.
Stir until well mixed at medium speed of mixer.
Spread evenly in pan and bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Place baking pan in center of oven.
Batter will rise in a short time, then it will fall.
Test with toothpick for doneness (not too dry).
Remove from oven and partially cool.
While still warm cut 24 squares and put on wax paper.

title: steak a la fitz
directions: Mix salt, pepper and sugar.
Sprinkle over steak.
Add Worcestershire.
Rub on steak surface.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine and mix into a crumbly mixture.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until top springs back when touched.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Cool slightly. Pour into baked pie shell; chill.
Wash and hull strawberries. Simmer 1 cup strawberries, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup water for 15 minutes.
Mix the remaining water with cornstarch; add to cooked strawberries.
Cook until thick; cool.
Add the uncooked berries. Spoon over pudding in pie shell.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Beat butter in a large bowl at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in flavorings.

title: white castle sloppy joes
directions: Sprinkle hot skillet with salt and brown meat.
Stir in flour. Cook for a few minutes.
Add undiluted onion soup and cook for a few minutes more.
Serve on dollar size egg bun.

title: homemade hot chocolate
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Mix 1/3 to 1 cup hot water.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: "Put them in hot grease.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Take them out of grease and eat them."

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add the first mixture with milk, vanilla, coconut flavor and coconut.
Grease and flour tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine ground cranberries, sugar, nuts and drained pineapple in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, just before serving, add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Combine thoroughly.
Serve immediately!

title: mom's bread
directions: Mix water, sugar and yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Make sure yeast is dissolved.
Add butter and salt.
Knead in flour; let rise.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, dates, cereal and pecans.
Form into balls about the size of a walnut.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: sugar-free spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container, or package into three 1-cup gift packages.
To serve, stir 1 1/2 teaspoons mix into 1 cup hot water.
Yields 3 cups tea mix (3 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: fruit compote
directions: In a bowl, combine the fruit. In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the jelly and water. Microwave uncovered on high for 45 seconds or until jelly is melted.; stir until smooth. Drizzle over fruit. Top with yogurt and sprinkle with almonds. Yield 8 servings, ready in 30 minutes.

title: creamy peanut soup
directions: Melt butter in pan.
When bubbly, stir in onion and celery. Cook until clear, not brown.
Add flour and stir until well mixed. Pour in chicken broth and blend well, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil, then turn down heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring, until blended.
Put soup through sieve.
Add cream slowly to the strained soup and stir until blended.
Garnish with chopped peanuts and a dash of paprika for color.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: marinated mushrooms *
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, parsley, salt, pepper, sugar and lemon juice in jar.
Add garlic and mushrooms.
Cover jar and let stand several hours or days in the refrigerator.
Remove garlic.
Remove mushrooms with slotted spoon and serve.
Serves 12.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Slice potatoes and place on bottom of casserole.
Add soup and celery to meat and onion.
Pour over the potatoes.
May add water or extra beef stock if too dry. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups hot water. Add gelatin dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water. Beat in sour cream and cranberry sauce.
Pour into 2-quart mold and chill until firm.

title: egg burritos
directions: Scramble eggs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Set to the side.
Butter pan and place tortillas on the pan and add cheese. Add eggs on top of cheese and fold tortillas into a burrito.
Add green chiles to eggs while scrambling, if you like them.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cut seeds out of peeled cucumbers.
Grate cucumbers and mix with cream cheese (room temperature).
Add onion, dash of salt, dash
of pepper, dash of Worcestershire sauce and salad dressing. Spread on bread.

title: baked filled potatoes
directions: Cut off tops of potatoes.
After baking 1 hour, scoop out inside and mix with rest of ingredients.
Fill potato shells, then bake for 20 minutes longer in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: super nachos
directions: Crumble beef and onion in frypan, stirring until lightly browned.
Spread beans in shallow pan.
Spread meat evenly over beans.
Drizzle taco sauce over all, cover and let stand overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Add cheese and let melt.
Remove and garnish with green onion tops and chopped black olives.
Spread with avocado dip, sour cream and rest of cheese. Top with parsley.
Eat and enjoy!

title: crunchy potato salad
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, cover potatoes with water.
On high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain in colander.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; refrigerate.
When ready to serve, mix in cold ginger ale (more may be added).
Top with sherbet.
Makes about 50 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: black bean and salsa salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well. Blend the salsa with the dressing.
Pour over the salad and toss well.
Cover and chill.
Spoon onto lettuce leaves.
Serves 8.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into baked pie crust. Bake in preheated 350° oven until golden brown, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in a 5-quart pan.
Salt and pepper to taste. When done, drop biscuits in pot and cook for about 20 to 30 minutes, with pan covered.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Mix both boxes according to directions on box.
Combine together mashed bananas and add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mama weaver's cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup water; add remaining water and milk. Beat in eggs and add sugar, shortening, salt and flour.
Mix well. Let rise 1 hour.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thick and spread with margarine, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll in large roll; cut desired widths to make rolls.
Place in buttered pans.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Top with powdered sugar icing.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Scald cabbage leaves.
Mix ingredients together and roll in leaves.
Pin together with toothpicks.
Place in pan and pour tomato sauce over them.
Bake in moderate oven about 350° for 45 minutes.

title: escarole soup
directions: In a large stockpot, saute the onions, garlic and celery until tender.
Add the chicken broth.
Add the carrots and let simmer for about 20 minutes, then add the broccoli, cauliflower, escarole and chicory.
Again, let simmer until these vegetables are done.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs.
Slowly add the eggs to the soup mixture, while constantly stirring the soup, until the egg mixture is cooked.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and croutons.
If the broth should boil down, add more broth.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Dice first 5 ingredients and mix together.
Pour salt over mixture and let stand approximately 2 hours.
Place in cloth bag and let drain over night.
On next day, heat vinegar, sugar, and spices to a boil.
Add drained mixture and let boil 15 minutes. Seal in canning jars.
Makes approximately 24 pints.

title: country style steak and gravy
directions: Salt
and
pepper
meat to taste.
Roll steak in flour. Place in
shortening
melted in electric frying pan.
Let fry for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Remove steak from frying pan.
Place in
a
2 quart glass baking dish with cover.
Set aside.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: multigrain buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix oats and orange juice.
Then mix in all other ingredients except blueberries.
Fold in berries.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400°
for 15 minutes.
I use the large sized muffin tins and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen regular or 1 dozen large muffins.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: Brown crumbled beef and onion together in two 9-inch pie plates in a 425° oven; stir.
Top with macaroni.
Mix 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce and water with seasonings.
Pour over macaroni and beef.
Toss.
Top with cheese and toppings.
Pour on rest of sauce.
Bake about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: beef over noodles
directions: Mix salt, pepper and flour together and coat beef cubes with this mixture.
Brown the beef cubes in a small amount of oil.
Add beef bouillon cubes and 2 teaspoons onion flakes and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Check seasoning to taste after 1/2 hour.
Add flour, if necessary to thicken gravy.
Add Kitchen Bouquet.
Cook egg noodles as directed on package and drain.
Add butter and mix through noodles. Top noodles with meat and gravy.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 (8-inch) terra cotta flower pot (or plastic). I you use terra cotta, line inside with foil.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll out on floured cloth real thin.
Dry for about 2 hours, then cut into long strips.
These noodles can be stored in a plastic bag in the freezer.

title: french toast
directions: Add milk and salt to slightly beaten eggs in mixing bowl.
Dip slices of bread into mixture.
Heat butter, margarine or shortening in skillet until hot enough to make a drop of water break into small bubbles and sputter.
Brown slices of bread on one side and then turn and brown on the other side.
Serve on hot plates with syrup or jelly.
Makes 3 servings.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Make a sauce with the soups, pepper, onion, milk and sour cream.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and layer half of the tortillas, half the chicken, half the sauce and half the cheese; repeat.
Make the day before if necessary.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then bake for 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in water to cover until tender; drain and cool. Combine dressing ingredients and gently stir in peeled, sliced potatoes. Makes 8 servings with 3 g fat per serving.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks (well beaten), buttermilk and soda.
Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup of boiling water.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt to mixture.
Add flour and beat 3 minutes.
Put in vanilla.
Add egg whites that have been beaten until stiff.
These are added last and are folded in the batter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Spoon into three 9-inch layer pans.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine and crackers.
Melt margarine and crumble in cracker squares.
Sprinkle cracker mixture over first ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix in bowl the pumpkin, carrots, raisins, eggs and vanilla. Mix in another bowl the remaining ingredients. Mix ingredients in both bowls together. Put into muffin tins sprayed with nonstick spray. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Makes 12 muffins.

title: quickie layered sushi
directions: Cook rice.
Line a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with waxed paper. Spread Konbu and Nori evenly on the bottom.
While rice is still hot, spread half of rice in pan over the Konbu and Nori mixture. Pack down slightly.
Spread diced Takuwan over the rice and cover with the remaining half of rice.
Pack rice down so that the layers will stick together and hold its shape.

title: potato rolls
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy. Add potatoes, salt and eggs.
Dissolve yeast into 2/3 cup warm water.
Add yeast mixture to creamed mixture.
Beat until smooth. Gradually stir in flour to make a soft dough.
Knead dough for about 3 minutes and place in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down and knead lightly.
Shape into balls and place onto a greased pan.
Cover and let rise for about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 45 rolls.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Drain well and cool. Cut bread into cubes and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Combine eggs, milk, cheese, salt and sausage. Pour over bread and cover. Refrigerate overnight. Bake the next morning in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and cream, alternately with flour, beating well after each egg.
Add vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven; turn oven temperature to 325°.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pasta a' figiol(italian soup)
directions: Simmer until pasta is done.

title: chocolate 'n oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° glass dish).
In a large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup oat mixture; press remaining mixture on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Top with remaining oat mixture and press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Store covered at room temperature.
Makes 36 bars.

title: chicken mexicana
directions: Mix chicken, soup and 1 can chicken broth.
Place chips in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan and pour chicken mixture over chips. Allow to rest 15 minutes.
Add remaining broth.
Smash mixture down slightly with a large spoon bottom.
Shred cheese and add to top.
Chop chilies, removing seeds and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.

title: oven baked beef
directions: Put meat into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine mushroom soup, onion soup and water.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 3 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease skillet and preheat.
Brown meat and drain.
Mix cornmeal, eggs, milk and corn.
Sprinkle corn meal on hot skillet. Pour 1/2 of batter in skillet; add onion, cheese, meat and pepper. Pour remainder of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: ham casserole
directions: In baking dish (8 x 13) place steamed broccoli, ham and rice.
In small bowl combine soup, milk, breadcrumbs, egg, 1 cup of the cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix to combine.
Pour into dish and mix.
Use reserved 1/2 cup cheese to top.
Place in oven 30 minutes at 350°.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix flour and pecans together. Melt margarine and pour into flour mixture. Stir until thoroughly mixed, then press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until brown (approximately 10 minutes). Cool. Blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip to form second layer. After first layer has cooled, spread second layer on top. Mix instant chocolate pudding and 4 1/2 cups milk together to make third layer. (DO NOT FOLLOW DIRECTIONS ON PACKAGE.) Spread third layer on second. Spread Cool Whip over third layer and sprinkle with nuts. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Yield: 15 servings.

title: carrot-raisin bread
directions: Combine water, sugar, carrots, raisins, cinnamon and butter in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cool the mixture.
When cooled, beat in the eggs.
Sift the flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture and fold in chopped nuts.
Turn into 2 buttered 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Bake lemon chiffon cake as directed; cut in 4 layers.

title: aztec salad
directions: Boil and devein shrimp, then drain.
In mixing bowl, place ketchup, picante sauce and honey; then mix.
Add red and green peppers, then stir.
Add shrimp and stir.
Boil pasta and drain. While warm, add to mixture and stir completely.
When cool, spread over bed of lettuce and serve with chips of your choice.

title: chocolate mint bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a small saucepan, over low heat, melt the margarine and chocolate. Stir occasionally.
Pour the margarine mixture into a large bowl. Add the sugar, flour, vanilla, salt and the eggs.
With a mixer at low speed, beat the ingredients until blended.
Pour into the prepared pan and bake about 35 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat milk and chocolate in saucepan until chocolate is melted.
Stir occasionally.
Combine sugar, salt, cornstarch, flour and cocoa in saucepan.
Gradually stir in hot milk mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and reaches a boil.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in one cup of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return all egg yolks to saucepan and cook until it simmers and begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked crust.
Top with Italian meringue.

title: easy english toffee
directions: Cook butter and sugar to brittle stage when tried in cold water.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
When cool, spread with melted chocolate and sprinkle with nuts.
When hard, break in pieces and store in airtight container.

title: apricot jello
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients; put spoonfuls of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen. My oven only takes 17 minutes.

title: autumn punch
directions: Boil honey, lemon juice, cardamon seed, cinnamon sticks, allspice and cloves together; let simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain juice and throw spices out.
Cool.
When cool, add cranberry juice, apple juice, apricot juice and ginger ale.
Serve chilled.

title: summer sausage-polish sausage
directions: Mix liquid smoke in water.
Add other ingredients and mix well with hands.
Divide into 4 rolls.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove plastic and place on rack.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: shrimp potato salad
directions: In a large bowl combine the first 8 ingredients.
In a small bowl mix together mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add to potato mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Boboli Italian bread shells, which are available in two rizer at most supermarkets, makes an easily prepared local, reduced fat, quick pizza meal or exciting hors d'oeuvre with the proper choice of toppings and can be served hot from the oven or at room temperature.
The following are some suggested toppings.
Your imagination can run wild with other variations using shrimp, crab, lobster, clams or diced scallops.

Remember to go easy with the oils and cheeses using only fat reduced products; a little goes a long way when balanced with other combinations of vegetables such as broccoli, zucchini, onions, bell peppers, artichoke hearts, etc.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown meat with onion and bell pepper.
Drain fat and add soups and water.
Stir and add rice and all remaining items.
Mix well.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: deep-fried artichokes
directions: Clean the artichokes, removing the tough outer leaves and trimming the stalks.
As each one is prepared, immerse it in a bowl of cold water mixed with the lemon juice to prevent darkening.
Drain the artichokes and dry them well.
Rap them on a work surface, so that the leaves open slightly; pull the leaves back.
Season the inside of the artichokes with salt and pepper. Heat the oil in a deep skillet to 300°.
Plunge the artichokes upside-down into the oil and fry for about 10 minutes or until crisp and golden, turning them often and pressing them against the bottom of the pan to open the leaves.
Drain artichokes on paper towels and serve.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil all ingredients together until it makes a firm ball when dropped into cold water. Pour mixture over popcorn and form into balls.

title: big blues - muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk to butter mixture.
Fold in blueberries.
Sprinkle muffins with a little bit of sugar before baking at 350° to 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef and cheese foldover
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain and stir in sauce.
Set aside. Unroll dough into 4 rectangles on ungreased sheet.
Overlap edges. Spread mixture lengthwise in a 4-inch strip down center of dough to within 1-inch of edge.
Top meat with cheese.
Fold shorter sides over filling.
Bring long sides of dough over filling. Pinch to seal.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Chop corn and add salt and enough water to cover.
Boil for 10 minutes and remove from fire.
Strain corn from the liquid in which it was cooked (there should be about 1 cup of liquid).
Add liquid to the scaled cream and pour onto bean egg yolks.
To the mixture, add corn, butter and lastly egg whites.
Turn into a buttered pudding dish and set in a pan of water (hot).
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Remove all bones and mix with cracker crumbs, onions and eggs.
Shape into croquettes and fry.
Serve with White Sauce.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Mix well the hamburger, macaroni, drained corn, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Put in baking dish. Layer top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour with baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in sour cream last.
Bake in greased tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Add chopped eggs and cheese.
Toss with mayonnaise and chopped onion.
Chill for several hours.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Blend well.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
(Roll cherries in flour first to avoid sinking.)
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then lower to 325° and bake one hour.

title: chili sauce for hot dogs
directions: Mix everything together except chili powder.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Add chili powder and cook a few minutes longer.
Can be frozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter; pat into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread mixture on top of graham cracker crust.
Layer bananas, pineapple (the acid from the pineapple keep the bananas from turning brown) and Cool Whip.
Top with pecans and cherries.
Refrigerate until served.
Cherries can be added right before serving.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together once the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, sugar and soda.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with mixer for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour 3 coffee cans.
Fill each 1/2 full.
Place cans on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and add next six ingredients.
Cook until potatoes are done and water gone.
Add sour cream and pour all into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with cheese and heat in oven to melt cheese.

title: chicken in the mud
directions: Layer in casserole, place cut up chicken on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour with foil, 1/2 hour without foil.

title: katy mcconnel's broccoli casserole
directions: Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian pupus
directions: Combine all ingredients, except muffins.
Spoon onto muffin halves.
Broil until cheese melts. Cut muffins into quarters and serve hot.
Makes 64 bite-size pupus.

title: glazed banana pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water.
Cook in microwave (in microwave container) until thick, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Add butter flavoring.
Fill any 8-inch baked pie crust or graham cracker crust with slices of bananas; toss the bananas in Fruit Fresh.
Cover top with whipped cream or topping.
Chill.

title: john's peppers
directions: In a large pan, cut hot peppers.
Soak for 3 days, covered in equal part vinegar and water, with some salt.
On third day, drain and add remaining ingredients.
Mix in pan.
Fill in jars.
Add oil to the jars.
Refrigerate.

title: e. c. mitcham's marinade sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Use to marinate any beef, pork, chicken or seafood.

If you intend to serve the marinade as a sauce, set some of it aside so that it never comes into contact with any uncooked meat or bring any that does come into contact with meat to a full boil to kill any bacteria that might be present.
Marinate meat 2 to 3 hours or longer.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: In large mixing bowl, add yeast, shortening and sugar to milk; stir well.
Add egg, salt and flour and mix well.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Work down with a spoon and let rise another 15 minutes. Shape into dough rolls and place in a greased pan or muffin tins. Let rise 15 minutes.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes or until done.

title: vanilla sheet cake
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and unbeaten egg whites and set aside.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and set aside.
Mix all ingredients, alternating.
Can add egg yolks, if desired.
Pour into greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: best baked beans
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Arrange bacon across top of mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: arugula salad
directions: Remove and discard arugula stems and cut leaves crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces.
Transfer to bowl.
Cut tomato into 1/2-inch dice; add to arugula.
Add onion to bowl.
Whisk remaining ingredients. Add seasoning.
Toss salad with dressing.
Transfer veal chops to warm dinner plate and top with arugula salad (approximately 1 cup).

title: mimma's oatmeal crispies cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, white sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and mix well.
By hand, add oatmeal and mix well.
Chill, then form into rolls and freeze before slicing.

title: sausage and pepper sandwich
directions: Pierce sausages with fork.
In skillet over medium heat, bring sausages and 1/4 cup water to boil.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes. Uncover; continue cooking, turning sausages frequently 20 minutes or until brown.
Remove sausages to plate.
To drippings in skillet, saute peppers 5 minutes.
Return sausages to skillet with wine.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer 8 to 10 minutes until peppers are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: king stubb's roasted pecans
directions: Put pecans in colander and pour a kettle of boiling water over them, then let them stay under the faucet and be under very hot water for a minute or two.
Drain.
Place a Turkish towel on counter with paper towels on top.
Put pecans on this.
Dry pecans. Roast in 250° oven for an hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread butter into them and sprinkle lightly with salt.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), 2 (9-inch) round or 3 (8-inch) round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat for 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake an oblong pan for 45 to 50 minutes; bake layers for 35 to 40 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool. Enjoy.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place crumbs over butter and bake for 5 to 7 minutes in 350° oven.
Place other ingredients in order given over top.
Do not mix.
Bake for another 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jack's diabetic cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix the egg whites, milk, nutmeg, cinnamon and vanilla in blender.
Add orange, rind and cereal; mix well.
Grind apples, bananas and carrots in blender.
Mix with cereal mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Cream beans, cream cheese, sour cream, taco mix and hot sauce. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle cheeses and bake for additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, combine ingredients in layers.
First layer is crushed pineapple.
Pour cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling and pecans on top of cake mix.
Place margarine patties over top of pecans. Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix.
Pour into lightly greased casserole.
Combine biscuit mix and milk; pour over chicken mixture.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Spread crescent rolls in buttered 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Seal perforations.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together and pour over the top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until done.
Let sit for 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: ravon's chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake according to instructions on box.
Cook in 9-inch pans.
Cook and cool.
Cut each layer in half with string technique.
Layer in this order:
1 layer of cake, 1 layer preserves, 1 layer whipped cream, 1 layer of cake, 1 layer chocolate icing, 1 layer cake, 1 layer preserves, 1 layer whipped cream and 1 layer cake.
Cover whole cake with chocolate icing.

title: german chocolate-caramel bars
directions: Heat caramels in 1/3 of evaporated milk.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix in butter and 1/2 cup of evaporated milk and nuts.
Put 1/2 ingredients in pan and bake 5 minutes. Take chocolate chips and pour over; add caramel.
Spread rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cajun catfish(for microwave)
directions: Rinse fillets in water and dry with paper towel.
Place in 2-quart or 10-inch microwave dish.
Brush with skim milk.
Combine dry ingredients and pat mixture on fish.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave for 3 minutes on High (100%).
Rearrange fillets and top each with a slice of lime.
Cover again.
Microwave for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes on High or until fish flakes with a fork.

title: ann's italian zucchini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in olive oil until clear. Add zucchini, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour into baking dish. Bake 5 minutes (do not let zucchini get soggy).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve hot.

title: almond cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly by hand.
Shape into ball.
Decorate with crushed almonds.
Serve chilled.

title: swiss quiche
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; crumble into pieces.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of bacon fat.
Combine all ingredients; pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: taco pie dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly on the bottom of an 8 or 9-inch pie plate.
Place green onion and salsa over cream cheese.
Top with chili and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes until cheese melts and bubbles.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: date jam
directions: Soak apricots overnight in juice.
Bring to a boil and simmer in juice until soft or just tender.
Whiz all ingredients in blender.
Serve on toast, waffles, etc.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in blender.
Add seasonings to taste.
Simmer over low heat until thick.
(The summer squash aids as thickener and extender.)
Can be frozen or put in jars, sealed and processed in hot water bath for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add strawberries.
When strawberries are thawed, add pineapple and bananas.
Put 1/2 mixture into large cake pan.
Let set, then spread sour cream over and put remaining Jell-O mixture on top.
Let set.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chip chop ham sandwich
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients and spread on buns. Layer ham and one slice of swiss cheese.
Wrap individually in foil and keep in freezer until needed.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes. Great to fix ahead of time and used for a quick meal!

title: calorie wise steak
directions: Trim fat from the steak.
Combine contents of envelope of gravy mix, hot water, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over steak in a shallow baking pan.
Cover tightly (use foil if pan has no cover) and bake in 400° oven about 1 hour or until tender.
Add green beans; cover and cook 15 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook with chopped onion until tender. Remove from heat.
Add butter, salt, pepper, cream of celery soup and soup can of sweet milk.
Return to heat and cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, margarine and eggs. Add cornbread mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes prior to serving. Serves 4 or 5.

title: tutti-frutti punch
directions: In blender, puree strawberries.
In large punch bowl, combine strawberry puree, fruit juices and pina colada mix.
Mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: trifle
directions: Prepare jello as directed on package.
Let jell for 2 or 3 hours, then add strawberries.
Layer cake, jello mixture, bananas, instant pudding (prepared as on box) and Cool Whip.
Finish
with Cool Whip and top with nuts.
Use punch bowl.
Makes enough to feed 15 to 20.
You may cut recipe in half.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Prepare roast by placing slits in fat and inserting a peeled garlic clove into each slit. Sprinkle dried parsley and salt and pepper on fat side of the roast. Place in a roasting pan fat side up with about 1/2 inch of water. Roast uncovered until medium rare.

title: no cook pineapple cake
directions: Crumble cake up in a long cake pan.
Make pudding with 2% milk or skim milk.
Before it gets thick, pour over cake.
Spoon over pineapple, juice and all.
Stir Cool Whip; spoon over top.
Cover; put in refrigerator.
Let set.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week or more.

title: cheese spread
directions: Chop all ingredients except cream cheese in blender with a small amount of water.
Drain and squeeze out excess water.
Mix with cheese.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: easy make ahead barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Cool completely.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool and tear into chunks and put into a punch bowl.
Make pudding according to directions and pour over cake.
Add remaining ingredients layer after layer. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: arroz con pollo (chicken with rice)
directions: Rinse chicken and mix it with the garlic and the orange.
Let it marinate for a couple of hours.
Heat up the olive oil, lightly brown the chicken.
Add the diced pepper, tomato sauce, salt and onion.
Blend 1 can of the red peppers in the blender with the water from 1 can.
Add to chicken the water from the pea's can and the asparagus' can only; pepper, bay leaf, cooking wine, chicken broth and 1 more cup of water.
Cook for about 15 minutes on medium heat.
Add rice and Azafran when rice is tender and chicken is cooked.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and green peas.
Place in casserole and pour soup over this.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick healthy snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Make small balls.
You can also roll in crushed graham crackers or chopped nuts.
(Infants to small children are not supposed to have honey; check with your doctor to make sure.)

title: low-fat mexican dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish, layer refried beans, sour cream, cheese, lettuce and tomato.
Dip with baked Tostitos.

title: italian beef
directions: Salt and pepper meat.
Crock-pot Directions:
Place in crock-pot.
Add all ingredients; cover and place on low heat for 6 to 8 hours.
Take meat out; slice and shred beef and return to crock-pot.
Cover and cook 1/2 hour longer or until desired tenderness.
Serve on French bread as sandwich or open-faced.

title: unfried chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, flour and all spices together in a bag.
Dip chicken into yogurt, making sure all is covered.
Then dip into flour mixture.
Place on baking sheet and spray the cooking spray directly on chicken.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: salmon noodles romanoff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Mix noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream, onion, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, salt and onions.
Place in a casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter-chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. With mixer, beat oil, sugar and bananas. Add peanut butter, egg and milk, mixing until blended. In separate bowl, whisk together flour and baking powder. Add flour mixture to banana mixture. By hand, fold in chocolate chips and peanuts. Bake about 1 hour in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Makes 1 loaf.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Combine cantaloupe, strawberries and grapes.
Combine yogurt mixture into fruit mixture.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.

title: stove top barbecue chicken
directions: In large skillet, saute onion in oil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil; add chicken pieces.
Cover and simmer until done; turn often.

title: mircowave broccoli-swiss cheese casserole
directions: Place broccoli, onion and water in shallow 2 quart casserole dish.
Cover with heavy duty plastic wrap and microwave on High for 8 to 9 minutes, stirring once.
Drain.
Stir in corn and cheese and set aside.
Combine melted butter, cottage cheese, eggs, flour, salt and hot sauce in blender and process until smooth (or stir by hand until smooth).
Stir into vegetable mixture.

title: sweet 'tato pie
directions: Cut and cook sweet potatoes until soft.
Blend potatoes.
Add sugar and cream in butter or margarine.
Add flavor.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake until brown on top.

title: caramel brownies
directions: In a double boiler, melt the light caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix the cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, melted butter and chopped pecans in a large bowl.
Pat 1/2 cake mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 6 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with the chocolate chips.
Spread caramel mixture, then crumble the remaining cake mixture over.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes more.
Cool to set caramel layer.
Cut.

title: fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces; wash well.
Put a half inch of cooking fat in pan and let it get hot.
Place chicken in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Flour real good.
Place chicken in fat. Keep turning until both sides are walnut brown.
Now cover pan and cook at slow heat 20 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Boil sugar, Mazola, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper for 3 to 5 minutes.
Toss with remaining ingredients.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs; add oil, cake mix, lime Jell-O (dry) and Seven-Up.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes. Cool and dust with confectioners sugar.

title: quick pineapple cake
directions: Melt butter in skillet; sprinkle brown sugar over butter. Pour a can of pineapple and juice over brown sugar.
Mix cake mixture and pour over pineapple.
Use any kind of fruit (cherry, peach, etc.).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: ranch baked bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage and add cream cheese and melt. Take stem out of mushrooms. Stuff with sausage/cheese mixture.
Sprinkle tops with Parmesan and bake at 350° for 15 min.

title: roast pork tenderloin with potatoes and mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle the tenderloins with salt, pepper and cumin.
Place the tenderloins in a roasting pan large enough to also hold the onions and potatoes in 1 layer.
Sprinkle the tenderloins with the sage, then spread around the roast the onions, potatoes, mushrooms, garlic and the bay leaf.
Brush them with the oil.
Place the pan on top of the stove and over medium-high heat cook, turning the pork and vegetables until they are lightly browned all over.
Place the pan in the oven and bake for 30 minutes.
Turn the meat and vegetables, basting a few times.
Pour off the fat from the pan.
Add the wine and water. Crush the garlic clove with a fork.
Discard the skin and blend with the gravy.
Return to the oven and cook 10 more minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ham trimmings or slices of smoked pork in microwave or conventional oven until crispy.
Set aside on paper towel. Combine all other ingredients, stirring well; stir in pieces of cooked ham or pork.
Pour into baking dish or pan and bake, uncovered, for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange almond salad
directions: Into large bowl, combine all ingredients and pour dressing over and toss.

title: mom's chicken casserole
directions: Put a layer of each chicken and bread crumbs until all is used.
Take equal parts milk and broth to moisten and dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: tomato soup
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Add 1 teaspoon soda. This will foam up.
Now simmer this for about 1 hour on low.
Add Sego milk.
Add a small amount of Wondra flour to thicken.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Combine with next 3 ingredients.
Put potato mixture in a heavy saucepan.
Add salt to taste and cover with just enough water to cook the potatoes and other ingredients until tender.
Pour off excess water.

title: brandied carrots
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place carrot strips in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or covered glass baking dish.
Stir together butter, brandy, sugar and salt and pour over carrots.
Cover and bake 40 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon. Add onion, green pepper and tomato to hamburger and simmer.
Mix together ketchup, brown sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce together.
Stir together all ingredients.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Can also be put in crock-pot.

title: rice casserole #2
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole and bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, roll out on cutting board, cut to size of pie pan.

title: firehouse chicken noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender.
In separate saucepan, mix canned ingredients; heat until warm.
Drain noodles.
Pour in canned ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° or in microwave until cheese melts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crumbs. Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle crumbs on top and drizzle with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time. Beat well after each. Add chocolate. Add flour to butter and chocolate mix. Blend well. Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato bake
directions: Mix together potatoes, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper. Next add grated cheese and onions.
Put in large flat greased pan. Drizzle margarine over top and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased glass oblong dish for 40 minutes at 325°.
Do not cream oleo and sugar or overmix.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Tenderize steak.
Cut
into
strips 1/4 inch wide and 1 to 2 inches long.
Brown in 1/2 of butter.
Set aside.
Saute onions and mushrooms in remaining butter.
Stir in flour.
Add juice from meat
and broth one at a time.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer to
thicken,
about 20 minutes.
When ready to serve, add sour cream.
Serve over noodles, rice or toast.

title: ginger and spice cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Cream margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and molasses; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mix in flour, soda and salt. Form dough in walnut size pieces; roll in sugar.
Bake 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes. Press down with a fork dipped in sugar.

title: wild rice chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice and onion.
Stir in rice, chicken and water chestnuts.
Refrigerate until cold.
Just before serving, stir in grapes and cashews.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate.
Fold into cream cheese mixture with pecans.
Spread into greased 8 in. baking pan. Chill until ready to serve.
Cut into squares.

title: quick chicken dinner
directions: Place butter in small mixing bowl.
Microwave at High for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until butter melts.
Stir in stuffing mix and parsley; mix well and set aside.
Unwrap broccoli; place on plate.
Microwave at High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, or until defrosted.
Drain and set aside.
In 2-quart casserole, combine mushrooms, rice and sauce mix, onion and water; mix well.
Cover; microwave at High for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in broccoli and chicken.
Top with stuffing mixture.
Microwave at High for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: egg pie
directions: Cream the egg yolks and sugar.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk.
Pour into saucepan or double boiler.
Add softened butter. Cook over medium heat and stir until butter is melted.
Pour into the unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: southern french toast
directions: Cut challah into 1/2-inch slices.
Soak thick slices of challah bread in eggnog (with or without whiskey) overnight.
In the same pan, broil to brown lightly, then bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine together.
Spread 1/2-inch on bottom of pan or dish.
Cream with mixer, sugar and cream cheese.
Spread 1/2 on crumbs; add pie filling.
Spread last half of cream cheese, then crumbs.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill for 24 hours.
Enjoy.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain bacon and crumble; save 1/4 cup bacon grease.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: suzie's stuffed shells
directions: Brown
hamburger
in
skillet.	Add
onion and salt and pepper to	taste.	In
large
pan, cook shells.
Drain and let cool. Drain
grease off hamburger.
Add eggs, tomato soup and 2 cups Mozzarella cheese;	mix well.

title: croutons with orange rouille
directions: Finely chop roasted peppers with next 5 ingredients in processor.
Add yolk and puree until smooth.
With machine running, gradually add oil through feed tube (can be prepared 1 week ahead; cover and refrigerate).

title: dirty rice dressing
directions: In one skillet saute ground meat and sausage in 1/4 lb. butter until brown; set aside.
In another skillet saute onions, bell pepper, celery and seasoning in 1/4 lb. butter.
Add other ingredients.
In large pan mix meat mixture and onion mixture together; mixing well.
Use natural gravy from ground meat and sausage to moisten.
Can be made the night before and warm in oven at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: bread machine potato rolls
directions: Combine ingredients according to manufacturer's directions. Process in dough cycle.
Remove dough from bread machine.
Grease appropriate pans.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and add Rice Krispies.
Roll into 1-inch balls and put on a cookie sheet.
Put 1 round toothpick in each ball, let them set in freezer.
Melt together in top of double boiler, chocolate chips and wax.
Dip each ball into the wax mixture and set on wax paper on cooled cookie sheet.

title: bulldog shrimp and green noodles(serves 6)
directions: Cook noodles; line casserole with noodles, make into a nest.

title: sugared popcorn
directions: Cook sugar and water to 270° or the hard ball stage (a drop of syrup forms a stiff ball when dropped in hot water).
Add any color you want and pour syrup over popcorn, stirring constantly.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add boiling water.
Cook until thick in microwave or on the stove.
Add butter and vanilla.
Great for hot fudge sundaes.

title: low calorie drink
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Serve over ice.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with dried beef.
(You may wish to make it 2 to 3 pieces thick.)
Cut bacon strips in half and lay on top of chicken or wrap around chicken and secure with toothpick.
Place chicken breasts in container on top of dried beef.
Mix soup with water (1/2 can water to 1 can soup).
Pour evenly over chicken.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: swiss birchermusli
directions: Pour the oatmeal and milk in a bowl 1 hour or so before the meal.
Put in the refrigerator.
Before the dish is served, add the berries and/or fruit of any kind, cooked or raw.
We grate apples and cut up bananas as well as the fruits and berries in season for our musli.
Mix all together with the sugar, oats and milk.
Try adding yogurt or juice from half of a lemon.
Good served for supper with coffee or hot tea, fresh baked bread and butter.
Serve in cereal bowls and eat with your spoon.

title: oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and peanut butter.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours or overnight. Roll into walnut size balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Put a canned biscuit in muffin tin.
Put 1 spoon of pizza sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Bake until biscuits are done.

title: toffee bars
directions: Separate crackers and place on cookie sheet.
Melt oleo and butter in saucepan.
Add sugar.
Cook 2 minutes.
Pour sauce over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Be careful not to overcook.

title: pumpkin-cranberry cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Combine cranberries and sugar.
Beat butter with brown sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and pumpkin.
Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto greased baking sheets.
Bake until just beginning to brown, about 20 minutes.
Makes 45 cookies.

title: nine day slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, green pepper and onion.
Blend with the 2 c. sugar and set aside.
Combine the remaining ingredients and bring to a full boil, stirring over high heat.
Pour sauce mixture immediately over cabbage mixture and stir thoroughly.
Put this into containers with covers.
Cool and store in refrigerator. Keeps well for many days.

title: chocolate caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
In a large bowl, combine popcorn and pecan halves.
Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, salt, corn syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat 15 minutes or until candy thermometer reaches 248°.
Remove from heat. Stir in margarine, baking soda, vanilla and chocolate extract. Pour over popcorn mixture.
Stir to coat.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 250° for about 30 minutes. Stir every 10 minutes. Cool and break apart.
Makes 11 cups.

title: chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add melted chocolate.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately in small quantities with buttermilk.
Add vanilla. Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Ice with Chocolate Buttercream Frosting, flavored with coffee.
Decorate with shaved chocolate.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into frozen pie sheet.
May serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water until tender; drain thoroughly.
Saute onion in 5 tablespoons margarine in large skillet.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese.
Heat and stir until melted; remove from heat and stir in cabbage, salt and pepper. Transfer to ungreased 2-quart baking dish.

title: sugar-free chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and fructose; beat in egg, water and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt in sifter.
Sift dry ingredients into creamed mixture, stirring to blend thoroughly. Stir in chocolate chips.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Spread tortillas with cream cheese, top with chilies, olives and picante sauce.
Roll up tortillas and wrap with foil; chill 4 to 24 hours before serving.
Cut each tortilla into small slices and serve.

title: dorothy bagwell's hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Do not let rise.
Cook at once.

title: green chillies and burritos
directions: Boil pork until tender in salt and pepper water.
Cool.
Tear up meat into small pieces.
Put back into water mixture.
Add green chillies, jalapeno pepper, garlic salt, pepper and salt to taste. Simmer.
Add more water, if desired.
Add cornstarch to thicken. Drain meat mixture from the green chillies and put into a bowl. Mash beans.
Grate cheese.
Lay the tortillas down; add meat, beans and cheese, then fold up.
Put in oven until warmed through.
Then, when ready to eat, pour some of the green chilli mixture on top of burritos.

title: gingerbread
directions: Place shortening in mixing bowl.
Pour boiling water over it. Let stand until melted.
Add molasses, sugar and unbeaten egg. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Will be very thin.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a
medium saucepan cook and stir soup and milk until hot. Add corn and butter.
Heat through.
Sprinkle with bacon and onions.
Season with pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Add all ingredients, except margarine and dressing mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine and add to dressing mix.
Spread on top of chicken mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fat-free angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until stiff but not dry.
Mix flour and sugar together; add to egg whites.
Put flavoring in.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.
Turn oven off; leave cake in for 10 minutes longer.

title: barbecue sauce for beef
directions: Cook beef roast in slow cooker until done. Cool to warm and shred out the meat. Place back into crock-pot, drained completely. (Meat should be salt and peppered while cooking.) In a separate bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well. Pour over meat in crock-pot and simmer for 1 1/2 hours at high, then serve from crock-pot.

title: old virginia hot wassail(hot punch)
directions: Combine cider, juices and spices in a large pot.
Sweeten with sugar.
Bring to a simmer over high heat.
Strain and serve hot. Makes about 16 (6-ounce) servings.

title: salad bar minestrone
directions: Slice any large vegetable into bite size pieces.
Saute sausage and garlic in oil in a large pot until meat is no longer pink.
Drain most of oil.
Add vegetables.
Saute 2 to 5 minutes until vegetables begin to brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, broth, water, beans and seasonings.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes. Sprinkle pasta over soup; simmer 15 minutes or until pasta is tender.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown chuck, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add drained limas and kidney beans.
Add pork and beans.
Mix all items together.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: pot roast
directions: Season flour with salt and pepper.
Coat roast with mixture, brown in oil on all sides in dutch oven.
Add water to top of roast.
Add onion soup mix and stir.
Bake in 325 degree oven 2 to 2 1/2 hours depending on size of roast.
Roast is done when it comes apart when pierced with a fork.

title: love on the beach
directions: Mix together as much as you'd like.
Add a touch of grenadine for color only.
Add ice.
Very good.
Enjoy.

title: chicken with blue cheese
directions: Roll chicken lightly in flour and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place enough butter in a nonstick skillet to brown chicken.
When chicken is browned, remove from pan and leave grease.
On lowered heat, add 2 tablespoons more butter.
Add cream and stir with a wooden spoon until mixed with butter. Crumble in Blue cheese.
Pour over chicken.
If you would like, use chicken strips and put on boiled pasta; then pour sauce over.

title: pound cake
directions: Start with cold oven. (Do not preheat oven.)
Cream margarine, shortening and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately again. Mix well.
Add extracts. Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: lye soap
directions: You will need a large iron kettle or granite one and wooden spoon.
Slowly add lye to cold water, stirring until dissolved. (Don't splash on your hands.)
Add lard and stir until mixture becomes creamy and thickens.
Add Borax and household ammonia. Continue to stir until thick and smooth.
Dip into molds or empty into cardboard boxes that have been lined with wax paper.
When it is cooled, cut into bars.
Let cure for about 10 days before using.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain the grease.
Add potatoes, broth, carrot, onion, parsley, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are just tender, about 15 minutes.
Combine flour and milk until smooth, add to soup.
Bring to a boil and keep stirring for 2 minutes.
Add cheese, stir until cheese is melted and the soup is heated through.
Garnish with green onions, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese, gradually stir in pineapple, 1 cup nuts, green pepper, onion and salt.
Chill until firm (at least 1 hour), then form into a ball and roll in 1 cup of nuts.
Chill again. Serve with crackers.

title: simple coffee cake
directions: Layer a 13 x 9 inch baking dish with 1 package of crescent rolls. Beat together cream cheese, egg yolk, 1/2 cup of sugar and vanilla.
Pour cream cheese mixture over crescent rolls.
Top with a second layer of crescent rolls.
In a small bowl, whip egg white and brush over the crescent rolls.
In a bowl, mix together 1/3 cup of sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Sprinkle over the egg white. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add egg, oil, carrots and vanilla.
Beat until combined.
Stir in crushed pineapple, coconut and 1/2 nuts.
Pour into a well greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or test done.
Cool.

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas in a pan; heat.
In a small skillet heat peanut oil.
Dip the corn tortillas in the oil to soften.
Put 2 tablespoons of the sauce in each tortilla.
Roll up and put in a casserole.
Top with the remaining sauce and 1/2 cup of shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: texas cornbread dressing
directions: In a frypan, add the butter, then add seasonings.
Saute until tender.
In the same frypan, fry and chop sausage until brown.
You can fix cornbread ahead of time.
In a large bowl, add all ingredients together.
Add the chicken broth.
Mix well and make sure it's good and moist.
Put in a large pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours until firm and golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: brown sugar frosting
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, butter and flavoring.
Add hot water until a spreading consistency.
Spread on cake when cold.

title: party pecans
directions: Spread pecans in an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish.
(They should overlap each other.)
Combine melted margarine, Worcestershire and hot sauce.
Pour over pecans.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and salt and stir well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels and sprinkle lightly with salt.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: hearty hamburger bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir meat and onion in large skillet until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in seasonings, beans and soup.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Prepare Potato Buds as directed on package.
Spoon potatoes onto meat mixture in 4 mounds.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp pilau
directions: Melt margarine	in
large saucepan.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Pour
in
rice
and
beef	consomme.
Add	more water, if needed, to cook rice.
When rice is done, add shrimp and continue to	cook until shrimp are pink.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: artichoke roma(makes 4 first-course servings)
directions: Wash fresh spinach thoroughly in several changes of cold water.
Discard stems and bruised or tough leaves.
Chop spinach. Blanch spinach in boiling water 3 minutes.
Drain well.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until blended.
Mix in Ricotta cheese and 1 1/4 cups cheese, breadcrumbs, spinach, parsley and garlic.
Shape spinach mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll spinach balls in flour.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.

title: fruit cake
directions: In bowl, combine egg, rum and water.
Add bread mix, candied fruit, pecans and raisins.
Stir 50 to 75 strokes until combined. Turn into 1 1/2-quart mold, generously greased and lightly floured on bottom only.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Half biscuits.
Melt together water, sugar and margarine. Pour over dumplings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Boil vinegar, water and sugar for 10 minutes.
Pour over drained pickles.
Stir with a wooden spoon several times during the day.
Leave in bowl overnight.
Put in jars the next day and refrigerate.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla; cream well.
Add the flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon and mix well.
Stir in the apples, walnuts and raisins.
Preheat the oven to 350°.
Pour batter into well-greased angel food cake pan.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn oven off.
Open door and let cake stay in oven for 1/2 hour more. Turn upside down; cake comes right out.
Frost or not.

title: keith's favorite pork chops
directions: The night before, prepare chops by sprinkling with tenderizer and garlic powder.
The secret is in the garlic powder (use a good amount).
I use a plastic bag (refrigerate in bag).
When you get ready to fry them, leave at room temperature for a while, then dip in egg (beaten) and flour.
Add extra garlic powder and extra salt and pepper to taste.

title: potato kolaches
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, potatoes and potato water.
Let sit 2 hours. Add
beaten eggs, butter, Crisco, salt and flour.
Let rise
30 to 45 minutes.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape kolaches. Let
rise.
Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen kolaches.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Dice fruits.
Slice grapes in halves.
Peel and slice kiwi. Add all fruit, including juice from pineapple in very large bowl. Layer with sliced kiwi.
Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Using a stir-fry pan or wok, saute shrimp and scallops in vegetable oil until the shrimp turns pink.
Remove and using same pan, saute zucchini, squash, mushrooms, onions, celery, green pepper, carrot, broccoli and cauliflower until tender.
Add shrimp and scallops; set aside.

title: lemon cake
directions: Pour mixture over cake.

title: fresh vegetable dip
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook bacon for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Allow to cool and crumble. Combine melted butter with bread crumbs and set aside.
Cook broccoli in a 2-quart pot, covered, at High in microwave for 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir.
While broccoli is hot, stir in soup.
Level mixture in baking dish and sprinkle bread crumbs over top of broccoli.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes in microwave.
Brown for 9 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Stir in oil, Hidden Valley and vegetables. Heat until warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in baking dish and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Or microwave on High for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.

title: peach cobbler (quick and easy)
directions: Peaches can be substituted with any kind of fruit.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, eggs and mashed bananas.
Beat 1 minute.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Mix until blended. Fold in nuts. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together well in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix Russian dressing, apricot preserves and dry onion soup together in a bowl. Line pan with foil (optional).
Dip chicken breasts in sauce and lay in pan.
Pour remaining sauce on top of chicken breasts and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Spoon sauce over breasts every 15 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine yeast and 1/2 cup lukewarm water; set aside.
Mix eggs, oil, salt and sugar.
Add 1 1/2 cups lukewarm water.
Add yeast mixture and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour.
Add 1 cup flour to mixture and beat thoroughly.
Continue to add flour, 1 cup at a time, until 6 cups have been added, beating with electric mixer after each addition.
Add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time and mix with spoon.
Leave dough in container and knead with hands for about 10 minutes or until satiny.
Let set at room temperature for about 15 minutes (or it may set to rise for 2 hours or until doubled in size).
Form ball and place on floured surface and knead slightly.
Roll out rather thin and cut into desired shape. Place on greased pan or pans and brush with melted butter or oleo. Let set to rise until doubled, about 2 hours.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 400° oven.

title: frosty fruit punch
directions: Combine fruit juices and sugar; chill thoroughly.
Pour over large cake of ice in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale and carbonated water slowly down side of bowl.
For trim, float twists of sliced orange and sprigs of fresh mint on block of ice.

title: frozen lemon pie(servings:  6)
directions: Beat egg yolks and gradually add sugar, beating constantly. Add lemon juice.
Cook in double boiler about 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix whipping cream until thick. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in thickened whipping cream. (Can use half of an 8 ounce container of Cool Whip as a substitute.)
Put egg yolk filling into either a graham cracker or vanilla wafer pie crust and top with cream and egg white mixture. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Takes about 24 hours to freeze.

title: feta cheese dip
directions: Crumble cheese into small chunks.
Remove olive pits and slice olives in half.
In a large bowl, combine cheese, olives and red peppers.
Add oil and toss lightly.
Add onion, garlic, vinegar, thyme, salt and pepper.
Toss again.
Squeeze lemon juice over mixture and let sit in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Keeps 4 days in refrigerator.
Serve with broken wedges of pita bread.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put sauce in pan to heat.
Add beef and pepperoni to sauce.
Heat on low.
While it is heating, cook noodles until tender; drain.
Mix noodles and sauce together and pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake until hot through and cheese is melted, approximately 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: individual pepperoni pizzas
directions: Mix meats together and fry until crumbly; drain well.
Add cheese and mix.
Put on party bread and bake on cookie sheet.
Top with a thin slice of pepperoni and black olive slice.
Bake at 425° for 7 to 10 minutes

title: veggie squares
directions: Unfold crescent rolls and layer on a flat cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Mix softened cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise.
Spread cheese mixture over baked dough.
Add finely chopped vegetables over top of cheese.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cut up chicken as for stewing.
Rub spices into chicken well with hands.
Saute onions, green pepper and garlic.
Place in deep pan.
Add chicken, tomatoes and 1/2 cup broth; cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add remaining broth and continue to cook.
When chicken is about half done, add the apples to thicken the gravy. Peas may be added at the very last so that they retain their color.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pie filling and pineapples into 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Mix.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling and pineapples.
Spread pecans over cake mix.
Layer butter over entire cake.
Leave no cake mix uncovered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter until melted.
Add oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: belingan salad
directions: Cook sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil and turn heat off.
Let cool and pour over vegetable mixture and mix well.
Pour into container and seal and store in refrigerator.
Will keep for over a week.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Pour 1/2 cake mixture in greased pan.
Add 1/2 sugar mixture, repeat.
Bake at 350° until done.
Glaze with confectioners glaze.

title: bami (indonesia)
directions: In a wok heat 3 tablespoons oil (2 peanut and 1 sesame oil). Add 4 to 6 pressed garlic and 1 tablespoon ginger.
Add meat and brown.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet (pinch edges together). Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: tavern bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat until coffee is dissolved.
Cool to 105° to 115°.
Transfer to a large mixing bowl.
Stir in yeast; let stand 5 minutes.
Add milk, oats, oil, salt and ginger.
Stir in whole wheat flour and 1 cup all-purpose flour.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer 1 minute.
Gradually add remaining 2 cups flour, stirring with a wooden spoon.
Divide dough into 4 well-greased 16-ounce cans. Let rise uncovered in a warm place (85°) free from drafts 1 hour or until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from cans immediately and cool on wire racks.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add dry corn bread mix.
Spray 11 x 9-inch glass pan with Pam.
Preheat oven to 425°. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: pecan-raisin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 cup sugar, margarine, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 egg.
Stir in flour.
Press dough in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake until edges are lightly brown, about 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in large skillet sprayed with Pam over medium heat.
Next, brown the onion and mushrooms.
Add the broccoli and cook, covered, until broccoli is tender.
Mix the cornstarch, soy sauce, brown sugar, pineapple, vinegar, spices and pineapple juice with water to make 1 cup.
Pour over chicken, onion, mushrooms and broccoli.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked instant brown rice.

title: turkey bacon roll
directions: Unfold bread.
Top with dressing, bacon, turkey, cheese and lettuce.
Beginning with short end, roll up bread.
Trim ends. Slice into 1 1/2 to 2 inch thick pin wheels.

title: japanese eggplant
directions: Ginger Butter:
Bring vinegar, ginger, shallots and garlic to boil in medium saucepan.
Reduce heat and simmer until almost all liquid is evaporated, about 15 minutes.
Transfer to small bowl and refrigerate until cold.
Beat butter in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in ginger mixture and chives.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Soften cream cheese in milk; mix all ingredients.
Spread in 8-inch glass pie plate and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Spread on crackers.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Prepare the ingredients and toss together.

title: salmon dip
directions: Place salmon in medium mixing bowl.
Add sour cream, chili sauce and soup mix.
Stir until well blended.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours; stir.
Garnish with red pepper star and green herb.
Serve with crackers or fresh vegetables.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: beef parmigiana
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Dredge steak in flour mixture.
Pound to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut round steak into 6 pieces.

title: homemade clay
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Next add oil and water.
Work mixture with hands until it is doughlike.
If it is too stiff, add more water.
If it is too wet, add more flour.
When the clay is a thickness that you like, knead in the lotion.
After you have made the clay you can store it in the refrigerator or use it right away.
Have fun!

title: tropical shake
directions: Beat together or whirl in a blender.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple-coconut chess pie
directions: Mix all together and cook in pie shell at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix all but last three ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix over pumpkin.
Dribble with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese blintz
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry rice in a little oil until brown.
Add all other ingredients to rice.
