Cover; simmer until rice is done.

title: grape jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in heated grape juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into desired dish or mold.
Chill.

title: skillet stroganoff
directions: Brown and crumble the ground beef in a heavy skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic as soon as there's a little grease in the bottom of the pan and cook until all pinkness is gone from the ground beef. Drain the excess grease. Add the mushrooms, broth concentrate, Worcestershire and paprika. Stir in the sour cream, then add salt and pepper to taste. Heat through, but don't let it boil. This is great as-is, but you may certainly serve it over noodles for the non-low-carb set. Yield: 3 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes.
Place in saucepan.
Cover with water; bring to a boil.
Cook until tender; drain.
Arrange in a buttered baking dish.
Combine and add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli and let cool, then mix all ingredients together, except butter.
Melt butter in pan and add to mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 450°.

title: company salad
directions: Chop or pinch lettuce into small bite size pieces.
Add all but one package of the almonds.
Gently toss.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Depending on how hot desired, you can use different flavors (mild, hot, etc.).

title: green enchilada casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook the ground beef until brown, breaking it up as it browns. Add the onion and Cheddar cheese.
Heat the tortillas just until soft in hot oil, then fill with meat/cheese mixture, roll and place in baking pan.

title: grandma's brownie cakes
directions: You also need cupcake liners.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Add baking soda to molasses and beat thoroughly.
Add the sour milk, shortening, ginger, salt and flour.
Let stand several hours to chill.
Toss about 1/2 of mixture at a time on a slightly floured board and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a cookie cutter dipped in flour and bake on a buttered tin at moderate heat for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Heat either in a microwave-safe dish in a microwave on High power for 2 minutes or in a heavy saucepan over low heat until warm.
Serve with chips. Makes 3 cups.

title: hump's egg rolls
directions: Brown meat over medium heat until no longer pink.
Drain excess grease from pan.
Return to heat, stir in Taco Seasoning, chopped onion and water.
Simmer on low heat and cover for 15 minutes. Shred 2 1/2 cups of lettuce, add more if needed.
Prepare egg roll wraps as directed on package.
Place 1 tablespoon of meat mixture in center of wrap.
Sprinkle cheese and lettuce.
Roll wrap and moisten edge with water to hold.
Set aside until all wraps are folded.
In 10 inch skillet or wok oven, heat oil over high heat. Cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce or hot mustard.

title: southern sausage muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400° (375° for dark nonstick pan).
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch.
Cook and stir sausage and onions in 10-inch skillet until brown, crumbling.

title: walnut dressing balls
directions: Cut or tear bread into 1/2-inch cubes or crumbs.
Toss with walnuts, seasonings, celery and parsley.
Saute onion in margarine. Add to crumb mixture. Add just enough water to moisten so mixture will hold together when pressed in hands.
Firmly press into 2-inch balls and place on oiled baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until crisp and brown.
Makes about 24 dressing balls.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat
oven
In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar
until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well. Combine
flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt;
gradually blend into
creamed mixture.
Stir in peanut butter or chocolate	chips. Drop
by
teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake.
Cookies will be soft. They
will puff while baking and flatten while cooking.) Cool slightly. Remove
from
cookie
sheet
onto
wire rack.
Cool completely. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare bottom crust and fill with tart cooking apples, sliced very thinly and sprinkle sugar over them.
Add water.
Distribute butter in small lumps over surface; sprinkle with flour and then the cinnamon.
Adjust top crust, well perforated.
Bake in moderate oven.
If preferred, top crust may be made of latticed strips.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa; add, but don't mix oleo and milk. Microwave on High 3 minutes until oleo is melted.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and spread in buttered pan.
Freeze 20 minutes or refrigerate 1 hour.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add egg and yeast, dissolved in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep a week in refrigerator.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cook rice.
Mix ingredients in casserole. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes. Will make 2 small casseroles or one large.

title: cream cheesy flan
directions: For Caramel Topping: In a 6-inch metal bowl, put 1/4 cup sugar. Heat on high while stirring with spoon constantly until sugar melts. When it is fairly dark, take off stove and set aside. In a blender, put all ingredients, except topping; blend well. Pour it into a metal bowl with caramelized sugar. Cover with aluminum foil. Put rubber band around foil and pan edge.

title: buttercream icing(3 cups)
directions: Cream butter and shortening with a mixer.
Add vanilla and food coloring if desired.
Gradually add sugar, beat on medium speed.
Cover with damp cloth.
Keep icing in refrigerator when not using.

title: chicken nancy
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place cheese over chicken.
Pour soup, mixed with sherry, over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle bread mixture over this, then drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: tuna mac casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese as directed.
In baking dish, mix drained tuna, onions, Miracle Whip, salt and pepper.
Press mixture flat in bottom of dish.
Place macaroni and cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through and brown on top.

title: cooper pennies(makes 5 cups)
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of salted water until tender (not soft), 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and combine with onions and green pepper.
Stir together remaining ingredients, pour over vegetables and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Before serving, drain, but reserve marinade for leftovers.
Keeps very well refrigerated.

title: gert's chicken casserole
directions: I use boned chicken breasts and cook in the stick of oleo in a skillet.
Mix the other ingredients and add to chicken and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and add 1/2 cup chow mein noodles on top.
Water chestnuts are optional but they give the casserole a nice "crunch." Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix stuffing mix, chicken broth and butter.
Layer 1/2 of stuffing mix in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover with all chicken mixture.
Top with rest of stuffing mix.
Mix milk with eggs.
Pour over top and leave overnight in refrigerator.

title: chili roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread evenly on the 6
tortillas.
Divide
and	sprinkle
pimientos,
chili peppers and ripe olives on the 6 tortillas.
Roll each tortilla up, cut off uneven ends and wrap remaining in plastic wrap, individually. To serve, cut
in
pinwheels
and
place
on
a plate.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Heat milk over medium heat, being careful not to let it scorch.
Add flour mixture slowly and stir until thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla. Serve with hot biscuits and butter.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
In a large bowl, cream the margarine and sugars. By hand, beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, alternately with zucchini, mixing well. Stir in raisins and nuts. Bake in a 350° oven about 10 minutes or until edges begin to turn brown.

title: almond chicken and rice
directions: Brown onion (chopped) in butter.
In baking dish, add consomm, can water, rice, almonds and mushrooms.
Stir.
Place salted, peppered pieces of chicken on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: hamburger barley vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in 5-quart Dutch oven; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables and barley are tender.
Remove bay leaves before serving.
Makes 10 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 20 minutes until tender.
Peel and cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients except potato chips.
Pour ingredients over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Top with potato chips (optional).
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mayonnaise cookies
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 30 minutes; form into balls and press. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 190 cookies.

title: broccoli-stove top casserole
directions: Put broccoli into bottom of casserole.
Put dressing on top of broccoli.
Mix soup and water and pour over stuffing.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: sugar biscuits
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add shortening and cream thoroughly. Add sour milk, alternately with dry ingredients.
Add soda which has been dissolved in a small amount of boiling water.
Add flavoring.
Dough will be very soft.
Roll out on floured board (not too thin) before cutting them.
Sprinkle generously over the top with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: miracle whip chicken
directions: Place 2 cups stuffing mix in a Ziploc bag.
Coat chicken with Miracle Whip and place in bag.
Shake bag to coat.
Arrange chicken in a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and soda.
Add next four ingredients gently.
Add flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baklava
directions: Grind walnuts and mix with sugar and spice.
Grease an 11 x 16-inch pan with melted butter.
Place 12 phyllo sheets in the large pan, brushing each with melted butter.
Sprinkle with 2 cups of nut mixture.
Cover with 5 phyllo sheets, brushing each generously with melted butter.
Continue this procedure until all nut mixture is used.
Finish with 12 phyllo sheets on top, brushing each with melted butter.
Chill before cutting.
Cut pastry into small diamond shapes.
Bake in a slow oven (300°) for about 1 1/2 hours until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and pour cool syrup over hot pastry.
Makes 75 pieces.

title: maine blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the dry ingredients (flour, sugar, baking powder and salt).
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat batter vigorously for 2 minutes.
Fold in with care the blueberries.
(Berries may be dusted with flour before folding into batter to prevent berries sinking to bottom of cake.)
Turn batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburg.
Cook pasta; drain.
Mix soups, pizza sauce, water, garlic salt and oregano.
Combine hamburg, pasta, soup mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, water, Karo and salt in a large skillet and stir over heat until the mixture reaches 235° (soft ball stage).
Add peanuts.
Cook and stir until mixture reaches the "hard crack" stage (300°).
Remove from heat and stir in butter and vanilla. Add the soda and stir vigorously.

title: grilled whole beef tenderloin
directions: Crush garlic and rub vigorously on both sides of tenderloin. Let set for approximately one hour.
Put tenderloin on grill on medium heat for about 10 minutes per pound, turning occasionally. Cut tenderloin into steaks of your desired thickness.
Put steaks back on grill searing both sides until done to your pleasure.

title: hunt's hamburger skillet stew
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, chopped onion, egg, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Shape into 16 balls.
Brown in oil in skillet.
Add vegetables, water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Pour over remaining tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer one hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove 1/2 cup stew sauce and mix with flour.
Gradually pour into stew and stir over low heat until gravy thickens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown chuck, onion and mushrooms in large skillet or saucepan. Drain excess grease.
Add tomato paste and dry spaghetti sauce mix. Add water to thin to desired thickness.
Season to taste.
Simmer 20 to 40 minutes.
Serve over pasta.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add milk, egg yolks and coconut.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour in baked pie shell.
Add meringue on top.
Brown in oven at 350°.

title: snicker brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup of evaporated milk; set aside.
Mix together the cake mix, 1/3 cup of milk and butter.
Press half of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan; set aside. In a large Dutch oven, over low heat, stir in confectioners sugar, butter and evaporated milk. Continue cooking until mixture reaches the soft ball stage (234° on a candy thermometer), stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Quickly stir in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla. Pour mixture into prepared pan and chill until firm, overnight. Yield: 4 to 5 pounds of fudge.

title: cinnamon-apple custard pie
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apples and toss lightly.
Add the 1/2 cup sugar.
Arrange in pie shell, cover with foil and bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.
Remove foil.
Beat eggs slightly, beat in cream, butter and nutmeg.
Pour over apples.
Bake another 10 minutes.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top of pie.
Bake 10 minutes longer or until crust is golden brown and custard is almost set.

title: calypso salad
directions: Cook seafood and place in bowl after cooking each respectively.
Squeeze citrus fruit over seafood.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Season to taste.
Marinate for 4 to 6 hours in refrigerator before serving.
Serves 12 to 20.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased bowl.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mary's italian chicken
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch baking dish; spray with Pam.
Cover the bottom of dish with thin layer of Ragu sauce.
Place chicken breasts in dish.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken.

title: double pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening in a medium bowl.
Add water until dough forms a ball.
Divide into two equal parts.
Roll it between two sheets of wax paper on a damp countertop.
Remove from wax paper and place into 9-inch pie pan.
Trim the edges off. Next, moisten pie crust and add your choice of filling.
Place the other crust on top of filling, folding the edge under the bottom crust.
Cut slits in top crust for steam to escape.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Serve with crackers.

title: grandma lamping's rye bread dip
directions: Cut out center of bread.
Use pieces of rye bread as dippers.

title: white floating lye soap
directions: Mix 1-quart of warm water and can of lye; let cool.
This will boil when mixed.
Use crock jar only.
Mix warm lard, ammonia and Borax, mixed with 1/4 cup warm water.
Add lye mixture to second mixture and mix good.
Do not use any plastic or metal containers. Use crock jars or granite.
Also use wooden spoons.
Beat until thick.
Pour into a granite pan or a small wood box and let cool. Cut and let set 5 weeks before you use it.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt. Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add sifted ingredients.
Beat, then add zucchini, vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Blend.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until hard ball forms in water. Place cream in mixing bowl; stir in hot syrup.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: artichoke bake
directions: Use marinade from 1 jar of artichokes to saute onion.
Drain other jar.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish (7 x 11-inch).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares when cooled.
Freeze, if desired, and reheat at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Drain vegetables, reserving liquid.
Set both aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in reserved liquid; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in reserved vegetables, half and half and remaining ingredients.
Cook until thoroughly heated. Yields 1 quart.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease 9-inch pan.
In heavy saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs with wooden spoon until well blended.
Stir in flour, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve these warm from the oven with vanilla ice cream.

title: mother's spaghetti
directions: Mix the ingredients, using half of the cheese.
Put in greased casserole and sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mother's white fruitcake
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter; add eggs.
Sift together the flour and baking powder, then add to sugar and butter.
Add flavorings. Mix everything by hand.
Add fruit and nuts.
Put into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: momma's blueberry selfish surprise!
directions: In large bowl mix graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon and sugar; mix by hand.
Melt butter; pour butter over mixture.
Mix until moistened.
Spread over sides and bottom of 13 x 9-inch oblong cake pan.
Bake crust at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Beat instant pudding with milk until smooth.
Add soft cream cheese to pudding mixture.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour mixture over crust.
Spread blueberry pie filling over pudding mixture.
Spread whipped cream over top of blueberries.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well eggs and sugar.
Add zucchini, oil and vanilla. Combine flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix all together.
Add 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: priscilla's pear pickles
directions: Wash, peel and core pears.
Place at once in 1-quart of water with 1 tablespoon vinegar added.
Combine sugar, vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add spices tied in a cheesecloth. Cover; boil 5 minutes.
Remove spices.
Put pears in hot pint jars.
Add syrup to within 1/2-inch from top of jar.
Make certain pears are covered with syrup.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath (212°) for 15 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in buttered casserole.
Place chopped chicken on top.
Mix lemon juice, sour cream, mayonnaise, mushroom pieces and soup.
Pour over other.
Sprinkle cheese and butter crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mock turkey
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix in other ingredients.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Blend and fold in Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: foil dinner
directions: Shape ground beef into balls.
Place in tinfoil.
Add potatoes, onions, carrots, butter, salt and pepper.
Place in oven or cook on grill or open fire.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough and cut into shapes on flour covered surface.
Bake at 350° just until light brown, don't overbake.

title: baked fruit
directions: Drain fruit and dry on paper towels.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar; spoon over fruit.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 325° to 350°.

title: gringo burrito
directions: Brown beef and onion together with salt and pepper.
Drain off grease.
Add picante sauce and soup.
Simmer 5 minutes.
May add splash of milk to thin out mixture.
Spoon meat into tortillas and roll up.
Place in dish.
Spoon remaining meat over the top and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter; put in kettle and add water.
Cook until tender.
Add consomme, pepper and flour (mix flour with a little stock). Simmer 30 minutes.
Place a piece of hard bread (can use toasted French or Italian bread) in a bowl; top with a slice of Swiss cheese.
Pour hot soup over this; also if you wish, use shredded cheese and spread over hot soup before serving.
Makes 4 - 6 servings.

title: reuben appetizers
directions: Combine ingredients; cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours on medium.
Heat in crock-pot for 4 hours on low heat.
Serve on rye rounds or cocktail rye bread.

title: golden fudge(butterscotch fudge)
directions: Combine in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan the brown and white sugar, butter and milk.

Place over medium heat; stir until butter melts. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture forms a soft ball when a small amount is dropped into cold water or until temperature reaches 238° on candy thermometer (15 to 18 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in butterscotch morsels and marshmallow cream until thoroughly blended.
Add walnuts, golden raisins, rum extract and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch square pans.
When cold, cut into squares.
The candy may be kept in a closed container.

title: spinach mushroom omelet
directions: Have everything chopped before starting to cook.

title: round steak sauerbraten
directions: Cut meat in 1-inch squares.
In large skillet, brown meat in hot oil.
Remove meat from skillet; add gravy mix and water. Bring to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Return meat to skillet, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf. Serve meat over hot buttered noodles.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Add jello to juice.
Add water. Heat to boiling point, stirring to dissolve gelatin.
Remove from heat. Add cranberry sauce. Chill until slightly thick. Blend in sour cream. Garnish with chopped nuts, if desired. Chill until set.

title: fruit dip
directions: Heat cream over medium heat until it bubbles around the edge. Mix sugar and egg yolks; stir in cream until it gets thick, 10 to 15 minutes and don't let it boil!
Stir in vanilla after it cools.

title: holiday squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter in large mixing bowl, creaming at medium speed until light and fluffy.
At medium speed add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
At low speed add flour and lemon juice or extract.
Pour batter into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Mark off into 20 squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoon pie filling in center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While warm, sift powdered sugar over cake.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: crescent quiche
directions: Fry and drain sausage.
Unroll the crescent dough and spread into a 9x13 greased pan, pressing the seams together.
Dough should completely cover the bottom of the pan.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over dough.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over all.
Bake in 425 degree oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy yeast bread
directions: Combine yeast with warm water.
Separately combine cup of water, oil, sugar and salt. Combine the two mixtures. Add flour and stir to mix.
Let stand for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Place dough on floured surface.
Make into 2 loaves, kneading very little.
Put loaves on greased baking sheets. Cover with damp cloth. Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown. Brush tops with butter after removing from oven.

title: corn meal rolls
directions: Bring milk to boil, quickly add shortening, salt, sugar and meal; stir and cook until mixture thickens (5 minutes) and cool. Add well beaten eggs, dissolve yeast in warm water and stir into mixture.
Add flour, mix well and put in refrigerator to chill. Remove after 1 hour.
Add enough flour to handle.
Shape into rolls.
Place in greased muffin pans.
Let rise 40 minutes, then bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes a lot.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, brown sugar and oleo and bring to a boil.
Add cream.
When 240° is reached, take from fire.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour thin on buttered cookie sheet.
When cool, cut into squares and coat each piece with paraffin and chocolate, melted in double boiler.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 2 cups boiling water.
Add softened cream cheese (use mixer to make it creamy).
Grind celery, apples, cranberries and oranges.
Mix all ingredients and add to jello.
You may use the pineapple syrup with the jello. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat the eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla; mix until thick and lemon color.
Stir in zucchini.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder; mix well. Add chopped nuts.
Coat two loaf pans (8 x 4 x 3-inch) with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing onto wire rack.

title: hawaiian pineapple chicken(serves 8)
directions: Wash the chicken pieces in cold running water and dry them thoroughly with paper towels.
Mix the salt, pepper and ginger together in a small bowl.
Sprinkle this mixture onto the chicken parts and rub it in with your fingers.
Lightly sprinkle on the flour or gently shake the chicken parts in a bag containing the flour.
Set the coated chicken pieces on a plate.

title: cheese and vegetable soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine chicken broth, potatoes, celery, carrot and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the onions, garlic, celery and peppers until tender. Bring water to a boil and cook broccoli for approximately 5 minutes; drain.

title: rocky road cheesecake deluxe
directions: Prepare chocolate wafer crust, pressing crumb mixture into bottom and about 1 inch up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Preheat oven to 325°.
In food processor, combine cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Turn machine quickly on and off in short spurts to combine, then process continually until smooth. Add melted chocolate; process until well blended.
Turn filling into crust, spreading evenly.
Bake for 50 or 60 minutes, or until set. Let cool, then refrigerate until chilled, 6 hours or overnight.

title: union station cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix flour, oats, salt and dry ingredients.
Add in this order:
Chocolate chips, melted chocolate and nuts.
Put in balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Put cider, sugar and salt into percolator.
Put spices in basket.
Heat and serve.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Shred carrots (set aside).
Combine raisins, celery, pineapple juice, mayonnaise, salt and sugar.
Pour over shredded carrots and mix thoroughly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into prepared pastry shell and chill for 3 hours or until set.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: devils food cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and then add eggs.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Add to mixture.
Add sour milk and vanilla, and last mix in soda and boiling water.
This is a very thin batter. Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a heavy 2-quart saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil (mixture will be bubbly all over top).
Boil and stir for 5 minutes more. Take off heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until completely melted.
Add vanilla and nuts and stir well.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into 30 pieces.

title: cough syrup
directions: Boil lemon 10 minutes.
Then squeeze juice into regular drinking glass.
Add glycerin
and honey to fill glass.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Stir well
before
taking.
Use 1 teaspoon as often as needed. Tried and good!

title: bosot
directions: Cook kielbasa; set kielbasa aside.
Using liquid from cooked kielbasa, mix all ingredients together until smooth, then add to liquid.
Stir until thick.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix the hash browns and margarine together.
Mix together all other ingredients, then add the hash browns.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Right from oven, punch holes all over cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Sprinkle coconut over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: wafer layers
directions: Mix instant pudding with milk.
Slice bananas.
Layer all ingredients as follows:
1 layer vanilla wafers, 1 layer of pudding, 1 layer of bananas and 1 layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers as the size of your dish allows, ending with Cool Whip on top.

title: green goddess salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the hot water. When cool, add the remaining ingredients. Mix together and put in container to set.

title: holiday fruit balls
directions: Peel onions and slice round.
Sprinkle salt on each slice. Place in containers in layers; cover with sweet milk.
Let soak for 2 or 3 hours.
Drain off milk; dip each slice in flour and drop in hot fat.
Have fat deep enough to cover slices and don't fry too fast.
Handle carefully so as not to tear them up.

title: lemonade or lime pie
directions: Mix the lemonade or limeade with milk.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Pour into baked pie crust and refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve in a hollowed out French bread.
Tear one other loaf and left over bread from bowl. Use bread for dipping.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Beat egg white.
Add brown sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Coat well.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Check while cooking.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Mix well.
Put in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crush Oreos until fine.
Reserve 2/3 cup.
Mix crushed cookies and melted butter.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze. Spread with ice cream (vanilla or mint chip is good).
Use any flavor your family likes, or make half and half using their two favorites.
Freeze again.
Spread with chocolate fudge and freeze. Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle the 2/3 cup Oreo on top; freeze.
If sealed tight, it can be kept in freezer a couple of weeks.
If no one knows it's in there!

title: dump
directions: Spread cream cheese on plate with hand.
Pour over sauce, then shrimp and chopped ingredients (to taste).
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Make 3 hours ahead, if possible.
Serve with Triscuits and Wheat Thins.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt cocoa and margarine in saucepan. Add sugar and blend well over low heat.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla flavoring; blend well.
Remove from heat, add pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Yields 1 pie.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla. Add coconut and nuts; fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 greased 8 or 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: microwave cheese sauce
directions: In a 1-quart glass dish, place butter, flour and salt. Microwave at High for 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute. Gradually stir in milk; microwave at High for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes, stirring every minute until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese and cayenne pepper.
Stir to melt cheese.
For thicker sauce use 3 tablespoons flour instead of 2 tablespoons.
Makes 1 cup.

title: gold bricks
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and water; beat well.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and baking powder.
Bake in a loaf pan and cool.
Cut into rectangles and frost on all sides.
Roll in crushed or ground peanuts.

title: broccoli and rice dish
directions: Mix together butter, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Top with butter, soup and Cheez Whiz mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Stir once about halfway to coat all pieces.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Put pineapple and juice in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese.
Put over pineapple.
Top with crushed crackers.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: grape leaf pickles
directions: Wash pickles and place in jars.
Mix salt, vinegar and water. Bring to boil.
Wash grape leaves and place 1 on top of pickles in each jar.
Cover with boiling vinegar solution.
Seal.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together ham and hamburger.
Add in bread crumbs, cranberry juice and eggs.
Form into loaf and put into baking dish.
Glaze often.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add vinegar and vanilla; blend.
Add margarine and coconut.
Place in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: easy hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef; put into bottom of casserole dish.
Add layer of sliced onion, layer of potatoes, can of kidney beans and can of tomato soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli with stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli. Combine eggs, soup, water and mayonnaise. Place layer of broccoli in 2-quart casserole.
Add layer of cheese.
Pour a small amount of soup mixture on top. Repeat layers until all are used. Toss stuffing mix with margarine.
Put on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: upside down banana cake(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350F. Melt 1/2 cup butter in heavy small saucepan.
Remove from heat. Add brown sugar and stir until smooth. Pour into 9 inch diameter cake pan with 2 3/4 inch high sides.
Arrange banana slices in concentric circles atop sugar mixture, submerging into sugar mixture and covering bottom of pan completely.
Beat 1 1/2 cups sugar and remaining 1/2 cup butter in large bowl to blend.
Add eggs & vanilla & beat until smooth. Sift 2 cups flour, 1 tablespoon baking powder & 1/2 teaspoon salt into medium bowl.
Add dry ingredients to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending w/dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes.
Spoon batter over bananas.
Bake cake until puffed and golden brown & tester inserted into center comes out clean (cake will rise above rim of pan), about 1 hour.
Transfer pan to rack and cool 5 minutes (cake will fall slightly).
Place platter over cake. Turn cake pan and platter over, inverting cake into platter.
Let stand 15 minutes. Remove cake pan.
Rearrange bananas if necessary.
Serve warm.

title: pink salad
directions: Combine jello and pineapple together and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook for 4 minutes.
Set aside and cool.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in medium mixing bowl.
Combine buttermilk and eggs, then slowly stir into dry ingredients.
Add melted butter.
Mix lightly.
Batter will be lumpy.
Yields 18 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: old fashioned salmon loaf
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving liquid.
Combine salmon and all ingredients, except eggs and liquid.
Mix eggs and liquid together.
Stir carefully into salmon mixture, mixing well.
Turn into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then unmold on platter.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in an uncooked pastry shell in a slow oven.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and celery. Cook until softened. Add cold rice and soy sauce. Heat, stirring until hot.

title: carrots-n-green beans
directions: Prepare vegetables and put into steamer to be steamed until tender, not overcooked.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown the first three ingredients in a saucepan.
Place in baking dish with beef consomme soup and 1 can of water.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: light and fluffy sweet potato pie filling
directions: This is enough filling for 2 pies.
Bake in pie shells in hot oven.

title: lemon glazed cheesecake(bon appetit - 1978)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 3 ingredients.
Press crust evenly onto bottom and sides of buttered 9 x 13-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 5 minutes; cool.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.
After baking, remove from oven and punch holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Then melt caramels and Pet milk together and pour over cake.
Let cool.
Then spread Cool Whip on top of cake.
Crush Butterfingers and sprinkle over Cool Whip.

title: double quick dinner rolls
directions: In medium size mixing bowl, combine water and yeast; dissolve. Mix in 1/2 flour, sugar and salt.
Beat with spoon until smooth. Add egg and shortening.
Beat in rest of flour until smooth. Scrape down sides of bowl; cover with cloth.
Let rise about 30 minutes at approximately 85°.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Stir down. Fill cups; let rise until dough reaches top of cups.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Blend chocolate and vanilla until well mixed.
Add each egg, one at a time, beating 2 or 3 minutes after each addition with an electric mixer.
Pour into cooled pie shell.
Top with whipped cream; garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: white cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add to sugar/shortening mixture. Add vanilla.
Chill.
Roll out on board and cut into circles. Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place batter in greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: diet cabbage soup
directions: Cook all vegetables until tender.
Eat all you want.
The more you eat, the more you lose.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juice, pudding and Tang.
Mix in fruit and put in fridge to chill.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate one day before using. Yields 2 cups of dressing.

title: broccoli salad by vivian weber
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and white raisins together for sauce.
Refrigerate 10 to 12 hours.
Fry bacon slices and the onion.
Put bacon drippings in the sauce.
Wrap bacon and onion up until ready to mix salad.

title: bread and butter pudding
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Butter the pudding dish and spread powdered sugar over it.
Lay the buttered bread over the sugar.
Beat together milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over bread. Bake in slow oven until light brown.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Halve (lengthwise) and seed peppers.
Fill each pepper half with shredded cheese and set aside.
Add biscuit mix and remaining cheese to sausage and water; mix well with hands.
Make a thin patty with the sausage mixture.
Center a stuffed pepper on top and wrap the patty around the pepper.
Seal edges and pinch off excess.
Roll each pepper in the Oven Fry.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: raspberry ricotta cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions on box and pour into pan. With electric mixer on low, mix Ricotta, vanilla, sugar and eggs. Spoon Ricotta mixture evenly over cake.
Bake cake 1 hour.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: salad
directions: Mix broccoli, cauliflower, onion and bacon together.
Pour dressing over; mix up and let set for at least 2 hours.
Before you serve, add grated cheese and mix.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Sprinkle with parsley and garlic salt.
Add tomato paste, 2 cups water, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook in large frying pan the butter, onion and celery.
In large bowl, put stuffing and cut up chicken.
Beat eggs.
Add celery and onion with eggs, then add broth.
Let set 1 hour.
Stir and add more broth as needed.
Can add a little sage, if needed.

title: chocolate oat-chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat oleo and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

In a medium bowl, whip the cream cheese until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, then add 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Continue to whip until smooth and creamy. Pour into graham cracker crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes. Remove from oven and turn oven temperature up to 450°.
Blend together 1/2 pint sour cream, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Spread evenly over cheese cake.
Bake another 10 minutes. Refrigerate immediately.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with toasted almonds.
Bake in a 350° oven until dip is thoroughly heated. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: rhubarb nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl mix flour, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl mix oil, egg, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients until moistened.	Slowly stir in rhubarb and walnuts. Pour into greased muffin tins or custard cups.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Grease only bottom of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen sides with a knife and remove from pan.
Freezes well.

title: old fashioned sour cream raisin pie
directions: In saucepan, stir together the sour cream, 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, egg yolks and raisins, stirring constantly until thickened. For Meringue: Place egg whites and cream of tartar in mixing bowl.

Beat until soft peaks form; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time. Beat until mixture forms stiff, glossy peaks. Pour warm filling into baked pie shell. Spread meringue over filling. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and arrange into "pizza" on pizza pans. Bake according to package directions and cool completely.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Combine cheese, salt, pepper and flour.
Cut in with pastry blender the margarine.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons milk.
Toss with fork.
Form into ball.
Turn dough onto floured board and roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Sprinkle liberally with sesame seed. Run rolling pin over again.
Prick dough all over with fork.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch sticks or 2-inch square and then into triangles. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
In blender or food processor, blend shrimp, gelatin mixture, zucchini, cheese, green onions, yogurt and dressing.
Cover and process until nearly smooth.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients except yeast.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cut shortening into flour mixture; then add dissolved yeast and buttermilk.
Mix with spoon until all flour is moistened.
Dough is ready to be refrigerated or make biscuits and bake.
Dough may be frozen until ready to use.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine in 10-inch pie plate.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Add beaten eggs and gradually add milk.
Mix well and add flavoring, coconut and margarine.
Stir well and pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
No crust needed.

title: german sweet chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter (oleo) and sugar together.
Beat egg yolks, and add milk; add to butter mixture and boil for 5-10 minutes, stirring constantly (burns easy).

title: spiced peaches(microwave)
directions: Place drained peach slices in quart jar.
Microwave remaining ingredients in 1 cup glass measure 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on High or until boiling.
Pour over peaches.
Allow to cool.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add milk.
Put in iron skillet and cook until it starts to thicken.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add a little chocolate mixture.
Add to skillet and cook until it thickens.
Add oleo and vanilla, pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: amish yellow angel food cake
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Add water, sugar, baking powder, salt and flour.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Fold into batter and pour in angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese and muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together; spread on whole wheat English muffins.
Bake at 350° until browned lightly.

title: candy mints
directions: Cream sugar, butter and margarine until smooth.
Add peppermint and food coloring.
Roll into small balls and flatten with fork or thumb.
Store in closed cannister on wax paper.
Nice for showers, weddings, etc.

title: hermits
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture, alternating with raisins.
(Add nuts, I don't.)
Wrap in Handi-Wrap or wax paper.
Chill at least 3 hours.
(Can be left in refrigerator 2 to 3 days.)

title: chunk ham fettuccine
directions: Prepare
fettuccine,
according
to package directions. While fettuccine	is cooking, cook peas, according to package directions;
set
aside.
Prepare
white
sauce,
according to package directions, using 1 1/4 cups milk.	Stir in nutmeg.

title: tomato toddy
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 2 minutes.
(Optional:
Dot with margarine or butter.)
Pour into cups and serve hot.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
As appetizer, serve with small crackers.

title: banana blueberry mini loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour bottoms only of three 6 x 3 1/2-inch loaf pans.* In large bowl, beat together sugar and oil. Add bananas, yogurt, vanilla and eggs; blend well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. Add flour, baking soda and salt; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened. Gently stir in blueberries. Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans. Cool completely. Wrap tightly and store in refrigerator. Makes 3 (12-slice) loaves.

title: ma jackson's orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 or 3 round layer cake pans.
Bake at 325° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into prepared tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients, except food coloring, in a medium saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until a ball forms.
Cool. Knead.
(I divide dough into several parts.
One portion for each child and have them knead the food coloring into the dough.) Store in airtight containers.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, egg and onion.
Shape into small balls. Place in a roasting pan and bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
While the meatballs are baking, make the sauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased pan or dish.
Top with 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: country chili
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine in a large saucepan until tender.
Add salt, basil, chili powder, oregano, thyme and pepper, stirring well.
Stir in tomatoes and beans.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 6 (2/3-cup) servings.

title: no-cook frosting
directions: Beat together 2 egg whites and 1/4 teaspoon salt with electric mixer until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until smooth and glossy.
Slowly add 3/4 cup Karo syrup and continue beating until frosting peaks.
Fold in 1 1/4 teaspoons vanilla. Makes enough to frost top and sides of two layers.

title: pecan drops
directions: Beat the egg white until stiff.
Mix in remaining ingredients, one at a time.
Mix until pecans are well coated. Drop by teaspoons on buttered baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: Boil eggs for 30 minutes or a little longer on medium-high heat.
Peel shell away from egg.
Slice with knife or use an egg slicer to cut eggs in slices (vertical or horizontal).
Mix diced onions and eggs together with mayonnaise.
Spread on a good layer of egg salad on bread.
Cover and cut in half.
You may garnish with pickles, if you wish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl and pour in 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: corn bread
directions: Cream together.
Bake at 350° until it springs back to touch.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugar, eggs and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add flour; mix.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Can double recipe.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter for 5 minutes. Add meat and brown.
Stir in salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook for 5 minutes. Add soup and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and reheat.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: low-fat potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender but firm; cool and slice.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add potatoes and stir until well coated.
Chill for several hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Pour batter into funnel cake molds.
Dip into hot oil (365°) for 35 to 45 seconds or until shell is light brown.
Remove from oil; tap gently to release shell from mold and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: curry cheddar cheese ball
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then roll in pecans.
Chill.

title: chunky blue cheese dressing
directions: Stir together all ingredients. Cover; chill.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip together cream cheese and milk.
Add confectioners sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into crust.
Freeze several hours.
Take out about 15 minutes before serving.
Refreeze leftovers.

title: peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place peaches in 8 or 9-inch square pan. In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients until crumbly; sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Serve warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pick meat from the bone.
Place chicken pieces in casserole dish.
Pour Stove Top stuffing over chicken. Pour 2 cans of cream of chicken soup (diluted) over all.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: country style barbecue sauce
directions: Saut onion in oil until tender.
Blend in ketchup, water, vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and celery seed.
Simmer 20 minutes or until sauce thickens.

title: rich chicken casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, heat the chicken, soup, milk and sour cream until very hot and bubbly.
Stir often as it tends to stick. Gently stir in the peas, salt and pepper and cheese.
Pour into a large casserole dish and top with unbaked biscuits.
Bake in a 425° oven until the biscuits are baked and brown.

title: quick pickled peaches
directions: Drain syrup from peaches.
Reserve peach halves.
Combine syrup, sugar, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves.
Simmer 5 minutes. Pour over peach halves.
Chill.
Drain.
Pierce each peach half with one whole clove.
Yields about 16 peach halves.

title: texas ambrosia
directions: Peel oranges, removing white membrane.
Cut oranges into sections, removing all membranes.
Sprinkle apples with lemon juice to prevent darkening.
Toss oranges with apples, pecans, pineapple, coconut and cherries.

title: hidden valley oyster crackers
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in a sheet pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 275°.

title: kitchen sink quiche(no crust needed)
directions: Mix and match leftover meat. If you wish, you can substitute leftover vegetables for the mushrooms, but if you use more than 1/2 cup or so, use a larger pan for baking.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Saute onion and peppers, in 4 tablespoons fat, three minutes. Add meat and seasonings.
Remove from heat; stir in eggs and mix well.
Place 1 cup corn in baking dish, then half of the meat mixture, then a layer of sliced tomatoes.
Repeat.
Cover with crumbs.
Dot with remaining fat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skillet green beans
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy skillet over medium heat.
Saute onion and garlic for 2 minutes.
Add mushrooms and saute for another 5 minutes.
Add green beans cut in 1-inch pieces.
Add water.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: herbed biscuits on the grill
directions: Mix the milk and seasoning in a bowl.
Add the biscuit mix. Mix well.
Roll dough out to 1/2 inch thick and cut out biscuits with a 2-inch cutter.
Place around the outside edge of the grill and loosely cover with aluminum foil, shiny side down.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Turn and cook for 2 minutes longer until they are lightly browned.

title: pecan pie
directions: Microwave butter in a 2-cup glass measuring cup at High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add eggs, corn syrup, brown sugar, flour and vanilla to melted butter.
Microwave at Medium-high 2 minutes. Stir in pecans.
Pour filling into pastry shell; microwave at Medium 15 to 20 minutes, or until sides are firm.
Center will be soft but will firm while standing.
Cool.

title: oatmeal jam bars
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture, beating at low speed. With wooden spoon, stir in oats. Reserve 2 cups of mixture for topping. Spread remaining mixture on bottom of well-greased pan. Spoon jam on top of oatmeal mixture to within 1/2 inch of edges (do not try to spread jam or it will tear oatmeal base). Sprinkle reserved mixture over jam.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, peanut butter and Rice Krispies; form into small balls.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on foil until cool.

title: salmon patties
directions: Open salmon; pour juice into measuring cup and set aside. Dump drained salmon into bowl. Add egg. Use fork to break up salmon and mix thoroughly with egg. Add 1/2 cup flour. Take 1/4 cup of juice and add 1 heaping teaspoon of baking powder to the juice; beat with a fork. It foams. Pour mixture into salmon mixture. Fry in hot grease.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make Jell-O; set 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
You can also add small marshmallows or top with whipped cream.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes about 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 8.

title: crab cheese ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese with mixer to soften.
Add pimento spread, crab meat and spices.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: deluxe brownies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cream
margarine,
sugars and peanut butter.
Beat
eggs
well
and add to batter along with vanilla. Blend in
flour.
Mix
well
and
pour into a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Place in oven for 5 minutes until chips begin to melt.
Remove from oven and run a knife
through batter in crisscross direction to make batter marble. Bake an additional 25 minutes.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Cook meat in oleo in 12-inch skillet until it loses its red color.
Sprinkle with half the spaghetti sauce mix. Then spoon cottage cheese over meat.

Then top with noodles in a layer and sprinkle with remaining spaghetti sauce mix, then basil, parsley and salt. Pour tomatoes, tomato sauce and 1 cup water over top, making sure all ingredients in skillet are moistened.

title: coca-cola salad(good for thanksgiving and for christmas)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in heated juices from cherries and pineapple. Then add cherries, pineapple, nuts and Coca-Cola.
Grate frozen cream cheese over the top of molds (gives the appearance of snow). Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue potato wedges
directions: Mix together last 5 ingredients.
Scrub potatoes and cut into large French fry-like wedges; baste wedges with butter mixture and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until tender.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion together and then add pinto beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Eat over corn chips.

title: chili
directions: Soak beans overnight and cook until tender.
Brown meat and onion together.
Add seasoning.
Use potato masher to mash.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion; saute until golden.
Add flour, cornstarch, paprika, pepper and salt; cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add milk and chicken stock.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until slightly thickened and there is no starchy taste.
Add vegetables and more seasoning, if desired.
Add cheese and blend well.
Sprinkle chopped parsley over soup before serving.

title: mushroom pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine cheese, bacon, onion and sauce.
Set aside.
Separate roll dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Spread cheese mixture on top.
Cut crosswise into 6 strips.
Place a mushroom at one end of each strip.
Roll up.
Secure with a toothpick.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes.
(Place outside down on ungreased cookie sheet.)

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook beet juice, sugar, vinegar and cornstarch over low heat until thickened.
Add beets and 1 tablespoon butter.
Heat.

title: unbaked graham cracker cookies
directions: Line cookie sheets with whole graham crackers.
Bring first 5 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add next 3 ingredients and mix with wooden spoon.
Pour on top of graham crackers.
Spread evenly.
Place whole graham crackers on top of mixture; frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: english toffee candy
directions: Put sugar in skillet first, then add butter cut in cubes and salt.
Coat well with sugar.
Turn to high, stirring constantly. When well blended with sugar, turn to medium and cook until mixture is deep amber in color.
Keep mixture from sides of pan so it won't burn or get too dark.
Pour into greased cookie sheet. When cool, brush with melted chocolate and sprinkle with nuts. Press nuts firmly into chocolate.
Repeat on other side when chocolate is hardened.
When all is hardened, break in pieces.

title: hot fudge sauce ice cream topping
directions: Heat evaporated milk, chips and sugar over medium heat, stirring constantly until chocolate is melted and mixture boils. Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into jars. Cover tightly.
Refrigerate no longer than 4 weeks.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Makes 3 cups sauce.
Great for gifts of food in fancy jars.

title: taco dip
directions: In a glass dish spread cream cheese on bottom.
For second layer, spread chili.
For third layer, sprinkle cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put in oven uncovered for about 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: great grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(Do not overcook.)

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook and stir hamburg and onion in skillet until hamburg is light brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except buns. Cover and cook over low heat just until vegetables are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Fill buns with beef mixture.

title: easy summer salad *(from gourmet magazine)
directions: Combine equal amounts of fresh tomatoes, corn niblets and green beans in a homemade vinaigrette.

title: chicken cranberry mold
directions: Blend mayonnaise, milk and salt.
Add chicken, celery, parsley, water and gelatine.
Spread on bottom of pan and chill. Take jello and add 1 cup hot water, crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup nuts.
Chill until slightly set.
Pour jello over chicken mixture and chill.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and
baking powder together.
Add alternately with milk. Add flavoring,	then nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
(If pecans are
used
in
place
of walnuts, use 2 teaspoons black walnut flavoring.)

title: easy oven-barbecued chicken
directions: Heat dressing, cranberry sauce and soup mix over low heat in small saucepan.
Stir until mixture is heated through, cranberry sauce has melted and all ingredients are smoothly mixed.
Pour over chicken breasts in greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.
Spoon sauce over rice.

title: microwave santa fe chicken
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Pound flat between plastic wrap. Place on microwave-safe plate.
Blend butter and lime juice in bowl.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with chili powder, garlic powder and cilantro.
Arrange lime slices over top.
Microwave, covered, with plastic wrap on High for 1 minute and 45 seconds. Let stand for several minutes before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Grease slightly an 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Spread dried beef slices on bottom.
Wrap each piece of chicken with bacon.
Mix together the mushroom soup and sour cream and pour over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours, uncovered.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: pumpkin pie(makes two 9-inch pies)
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells, unbaked.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake pies for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° and bake 45 minutes more or until knife comes out clean (butter knife inserted in middle of pie).

title: black and blue salad
directions: Mix well.
Spread over congealed jello.
Sprinkle top with pecans, walnuts, coconut or any type of garnish.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients and place in prepared pie shell. Bake at 375° until crust is brown and knife comes out clean when inserted in middle of pie!
Can garnish with pecan halves, if necessary.

title: sour cream supreme
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, sugar and pepper. Mix in tomato sauce. Simmer 20 minutes.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Cook water, sugar and corn starch until thick. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over apples. Mix together topping ingredients and put on apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Cook and drain ground beef as if making tacos.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Add water if needed.)
Simmer for 1 hour or longer. Serves 4 to 6 people.
Serve with cornbread.

title: double cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch baking pan. Sift flour with cornmeal, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, milk, butter and corn.

Add flour mixture, stirring only until flour mixture is moistened. Spoon batter into prepared pan; bake 25 to 30 minutes, or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean and top is golden brown.
Spread butter or margarine on top, as this makes it soft and moist.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot.
Makes about 9 servings. This is Ray Watley's favorite.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Chill Pet milk in tray until almost frozen at edges.
Mix cream cheese in a large bowl until creamy.
Stir in all the fruits.
Put cold milk into a chilled bowl and whip until fluffy at high speed.
Add lemon juice and whip stiff.
Fold
into fruit mixture.
Put into a 9-inch square pan.
Freeze until firm.
Can serve on lettuce leaves.

title: raisin and pecan cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix the first 5 ingredients and heat until margarine is melted.
Remove from heat.
Separate eggs; set aside the whites in a grease-free bowl.
Maintain them at room temperature.
Slowly add 8 tablespoons of heated liquid to the egg yolks.
Stir constantly.
Pour yolks into remainder of heated mixture.
Dissolve cornstarch in the 1/2 cup of water.
Then add to the milk and egg mixture.
Over medium heat, bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate until cool.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Peel and slice potatoes; boil for approximately 5 to 8 minutes. While potatoes are boiling, grease an 8-inch square baking dish. In a medium saucepan, combine the cornstarch, milk, salt, pepper and butter and bring to a boil, stirring constantly until sauce thickens, about 5 minutes. Once sauce thickens, stir in 2 cups of the shredded cheese. Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and 1/4 cup shredded cheese. Bake in preheated oven until brown (about 30 to 40 minutes).

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and let chill for a few hours before using.
Lasts 3 to 5 days.

title: sausage wontons
directions: Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Place wonton wraps in pan and spray with Pam.
Broil for 1 minute or until wonton is light brown.
Take wraps out of pan and place on cookie sheet.
Fill with mixture of sausage, cheeses and dressing.
Broil until cheese melts and wraps are golden brown.

title: impossible mexican pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate pan.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in skillet until done.
Drain; stir in seasoning mix.
Spread beef mixture in pie plate.
Sprinkle with cheese and chilies.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed.
Pour into pie plate over mixture.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: five bean salad
directions: Drain canned beans.
Combine beans, onion rings and green pepper.
Put remaining ingredients in a screw top jar.
Cover tightly and shake well to blend.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Drain before serving. Serves 25 to 30.

title: pineapple apricot salad
directions: Drain and chill fruit.
Reserve 1 cup of juice for topping. Mix Jell-O by package directions.
Add juice to Jell-O and chill until thick.
Add marshmallows and fruit when jelled.

title: onion ice cream
directions: Combine first six ingredients in saucepan and cook thick. Stir in beaten egg and vinegar. Cool thoroughly. Fold in remaining ingredients. Freeze firm. Use with vegetables salads or tomatoes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Clean shrimp, leaving tails.
Cut along back.
Cut into shrimp about 1 inch where head was.
Mix all ingredients together; marinate overnight in glass bowl (not metal).
Place butter in pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 450° until pink.
Sprinkle with additional parsley and oregano for color.

title: harriet's pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and butter; cream in sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Alternate milk and flour; mix well. Add vanilla and butter flavorings. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: beef and barley soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven or kettle, heat oil over medium heat. Brown beef.
Add onion, carrots, celery, tomatoes, water and bouillon; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours or until beef is tender.
Add barley; simmer another 50 to 60 minutes or until the barley is done.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: carrot bake
directions: Place carrots, onions, and garlic into greased 15x10 in. baking pan.
Drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Sprinkle with thyme, salt, and pepper,
Gently toss to coat.
Cover and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Stir. Bake uncovered for 10 minutes; stir again. Bake 10 minutes longer or until carrots are crisp-tender.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda; allow to cool. Cream shortening with cane sugar.
Add well-beaten eggs.
Add cooled date mixture. Sift together all-purpose flour with salt and soda. Combine with mixture. Mix well and pour into oblong cake pan. Top with the following before baking.

title: easy microwave fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in large glass bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap.

title: dream squares
directions: Cream the butter
with the sugar.

Blend in flour and press mixture evenly over bottom of ungreased 9-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. While cooking, mix the eggs (beaten), 1 cup brown sugar, 1 tablespoon flour, salt, baking powder, coconut and chopped nuts.
Spread on top of the first mixture. Bake 20 minutes longer. Cool and cut in 16 squares.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.
Add cheese and bell pepper to mix, if desired.

title: orange delight
directions: Drain pineapple; pour juice in cup and fill to 2 cups.
Boil and pour over Jell-O.
Refrigerate until almost jelled.
Mix pineapple, cheese and marshmallows together; set aside.
When Jell-O is almost jelled, beat with mixer until fluffy.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip; mix on low speed.
Add to pineapple mixture by hand. Stir in remaining Cool Whip.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Stir in peaches and lemon juice.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Beat and stir 1 minute.
Pour into unbuttered, 2-quart casserole.
Keep hot in 400° oven.

title: turkey fajitas
directions: In medium bowl, combine turkey strips, lime juice, garlic, oregano and cumin.
Let stand, covered, for 1 hour to blend flavors.
Spray a medium nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Saute onion and bell pepper until tender.
Add turkey to skillet; cook until heated through, about 3 minutes.
In preheated toaster oven or microwave oven, heat tortillas, following label directions.
Spoon 1/4 of the turkey mixture onto each tortilla; top each with 1 ounce cheese and 1 tablespoon picante sauce.
Fold tortilla over filling.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Brown in oven at 350° until brown.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat 2 minutes, stirring until mixture boils.
Remove from heat; cool. Add confectioners sugar gradually, beating after each addition until thick enough to spread.

title: caramel pie
directions: Add the ingredients together and cook in a double boiler until thick.
Meanwhile, burn 1/4 cup sugar in a skillet.
Pour burnt sugar into other mixture and beat.
Pour into pie shell and top with whipped egg whites and brown top in oven.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix soup, corn and taco mix.
Spray Pam in large baking dish and put chicken in.
Pour over sauce.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serve with salsa, Spanish rice, refried beans and hot corn tortillas and butter.

title: preacher pie
directions: Pour into crust.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pork chop dish
directions: Mix 1 cup bread crumbs and onion mix.
Beat 1 egg.
Dip pork chops that have been salted in egg mixture and roll in crumbs. Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is good on chicken also.

title: crab meat and asparagus soup
directions: Bring stock to a boil.
Add salt and ginger.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Stir in dissolved cornstarch; cook 30 seconds.
Add eggs, stirring constantly in circular motion.
Remove from heat. Sprinkle chopped scallion and pepper on top.

title: pecan logs
directions: In a large bowl, place butter and microwave on High for 1 minute until melted into butter.
Mix brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir well.
Blend in nuts and pancake mix.
Center will not be quite set but will be firm upon cooling.
When cool enough to handle, cut into long thin bars and roll in powdered sugar. Microwave on High for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: famous fudge
directions: Before you begin, crisp nuts.
Cut marshmallows, using scissors dipped in cold water.
Line 8 x 11-inch pan with foil and butter foil.
Combine sugar, milk and oleo (cut into thin slices) in a 4-quart heavy saucepan.
Place over medium heat.
Stir constantly with wooden spoon until mixture comes to a full boil. Allow to boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows and stir until marshmallows have dissolved and mixture is smooth.
Add vanilla.
Add milk chocolate and semi-sweet chocolate chips and stir again until mixture is smooth. Blend in nuts; pour into pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares or store loosely uncut in foil for up to 1 month in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly in sauce pan until jelly melts. Add wieners cut in bite size. Heat thoroughly. Serve warm.

title: chocolate plunge
directions: Bring syrup and cream to boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips.
Stir until completely melted.
Serve warm as a dip for fruit.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: bohemian pound cake
directions: Cream
Crisco,
sugar
and
brown
sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 15x10 jelly roll pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add pizza sauce, salt, pepper, Italian seasoning.
Add to meat and sauce 2 cups of drained, cooked macaroni, including the milk and beaten egg in the macaroni.

title: grandma's special sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Cut in margarine as for pie crust.
Add vanilla.
In separate bowl, beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Beat thoroughly and mix with sifted mixture.
Roll out, cut and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° until lightly browned.
Easy and oh so good.

title: english sultana tea scones(golden raisins)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Rub butter into flour lightly.
Add sugar and raisins and mix to a soft paste with the milk.
Be careful not to make mixture too wet.

title: mini chip blondies
directions: Cream butter or margarine and brown sugar in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well. In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in mini chips.
Spread batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool completely in pan.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: salsa
directions: Combine tomatoes, green onions, garlic, pepper, oil and lime juice in a medium bowl.
Stir in cilantro, if desired.
Season with salt, sugar and pepper.
Adjust seasonings to taste, adding lime juice or chili pepper, if desired.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: brazil nut coffee cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and 3
teaspoons
cinnamon	into large bowl.
Add butter and Crisco, while egg and
egg	yolk.
With
electric mixer on low speed mix well.
Turn into 15
1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread evenly with spatula or pat with hands.
With fork beat
egg white
slightly;	brush
over
dough.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup sugar,
teaspoon
cinnamon
and	nuts and sprinkle over top of dough.
Bake 25 minutes or until nuts are golden brown. Cool in pan; cut into 2 x 1 inch bars.
Makes 6 dozen depending on size of cuts.
Do not overcook.

title: apple-cranberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 350°.
Cut slits in top.
Bake approximately 40 minutes, golden brown.
Makes large juicy very good pie!

title: apricot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a large bowl mix apricot preserves, dressing and soup mix.
Place chicken breasts in a large oven-proof baking dish. Pour apricot mixture evenly over chicken.
Bake uncovered for two hours.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with large size corn chips to scoop.

title: macaroni corn casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and place in baking dish. Place oleo in chunks on top. The salt and pepper should be stirred in first. Bake in a 350° oven, uncovered, 1/2 hour and covered for 1/2 hour longer.
Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: kalamara yemista(stuffed squid)
directions: Wash and clean squid, remove ink bag and skin.
Cut off tentacles and set aside.
In a large skillet, heat oil and brown scallions, garlic, and parsley.
Add chopped tentacles and brown; add oregano, wine and more oil, if needed to braise.
Add spinach and rice; simmer for 20 minutes.
Stuff squid loosely with the rice mixture; arrange in skillet.
Add lemon juice, broth, 1/2 cup oil and 1 cup water.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cool; slice carefully into 1/2-inch rings and arrange on a platter.
Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: cherried fruit compote(delicious topped with whipped cream, custard sauce or yogurt.)
directions: In medium bowl, stir sherry, juice and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Toss with fruit to coat.
Cover and chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except dressing.
Store in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Add dressing and serve.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix together chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter.
Melt together over medium heat.
Pour mixture over Rice Chex.
Shake powdered sugar over preceding combined ingredients.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Combine melted margarine with ground pretzels; mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: j and k's party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix all of the ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into baking pan and bake for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cool before serving.
