Store in airtight container.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar and pudding mix in a large bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in oats, chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: raisin-spice bars
directions: Boil raisins in water, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add butter to hot raisins and water and allow to melt.
Add sugar and beaten egg; stir well to dissolve sugar.
Combine remaining dry ingredients and add to raisin mixture.
Stir until well mixed, but do not beat.
Pour batter into greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. If desired, frost with orange or lemon icing while still hot, then let cool and cut into squares.

title: comeback sauce
directions: Small recipe makes around 2 cups.
A good sauce for crayfish or lobster.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Mix as you go.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pecan tassies
directions: For pastry, in mixing bowl, cream together the 1/2 cup butter or margarine and cream cheese.
Stir in flour; mix well.
Cover and chill mixture about 1 hour.
In small mixing bowl, stir together egg, brown sugar, 1 tablespoon butter, vanilla and salt just until smooth; set aside.
Shape chilled pastry dough into two dozen 1-inch balls; place each ball in ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin cup.
Press dough into bottom and sides of cups.
Spoon about 1 teaspoon of the chopped nuts into each pastry-lined muffin cup; fill each with egg mixture.
Bake in 325° oven for about 25 minutes or until filling is set.
Cool; remove from pans.
Cover. Store in container.
Makes 24.

title: apricot-yogurt cheese topping(for pancakes)
directions: Line colander with several layers of cheesecloth and set over medium-size bowl.
Pour yogurt into colander; let stand for 1 or 2 hours, until liquid drains.
Cover all with plastic wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook
chicken
until done (save broth).
Cut up in small pieces
and
put
on bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup and 1 cup milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with 1 stick butter and 1 cup water or broth.
Toss gently and place in 2 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco pie
directions: Lightly grease 9-inch pie plate or 9x9-inch square pan. Brown beef, onions, and peppers.
Add taco seasoning.
Pour into prepared pan.
In a separate bowl, combine Bisquick, eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over beef mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: chicken francaises (in the pan)
directions: Put floured chicken breasts into beaten eggs.
Place in frying pan on high heat with oil covering the bottom half inch.

title: pretty layered salad
directions: Makes a large salad.
Serves about 20.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Thaw slightly hash browns and spread in 9 x 13-inch dish. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix butter, cheese, soup, sour cream and onion.
Pour over potatoes.
Put corn flakes in 1 stick melted butter in separate bowl and sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Into container, put all ingredients, except hot milk.
Cover. Blend 30 seconds on button 3 (chop).
After 5 seconds, remove cover and gradually pour in hot milk.

title: pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Cook together the juice from pineapple, sugar, flour, eggs and water.
Cook until thick.
Let cool completely.
Mix together with the pineapple, marshmallows and cheese.
Chill.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Let cool and pick meat off bones and set aside.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy on slow mix. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix after each one.
Add flour and whipping cream alternately, a little at a time; add vanilla.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Turn temperature to 300°.
Bake for a total of 1 1/2 hours.
Do not peep.

title: roll out sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into desired shapes and bake at 375° for 8-10 minutes.
You do not need to refrigerate before baking.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, oatmeal, sugar, salt and cinnamon together.
Layer apples in a shallow pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Sprinkle dry mixture over top of apples.
Pour melted margarine over crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: grommie's homemade bread
directions: Mix lukewarm water with sugar and yeast in a large bowl until dissolved.
Soften butter in lukewarm milk and add this with potato water to yeast mixture.
Stir well.
Gradually stir in flour to mixture one cup at a time.
Stir until dough pulls away from the side of the bowl and forms a ball.
Knead on well floured surface until smooth and elastic, approximately 5 minutes or 100 times.
Put in greased bowl; cover and let rise away from drafts. Punch down when indent remains when touched, approximately 1 hour. Divide dough in 2 sections.
Knead; place in greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes and golden brown.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Use a large pie plate.
Fill pie tin 2/3 full of apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon, brown sugar and 1 tablespoon sugar on apples.
Set aside.
In a medium pan, combine butter, sugar and flour.
Add 1 egg, beaten, and a pinch of salt and spread over the apples.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll out on floured wax paper.
Pick up paper and place over 10-inch pie plate.
Peel off wax paper. Put in preheated 400° oven and bake while mixing filling.

title: corn fritters
directions: Place corn in bowl with beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add. Beat until smooth. Drop in fat fryer.
Cook to a golden brown.

title: pecan dip
directions: Put orange juice concentrate, cream cheese and pecans in a blender or work bowl of food processor.
Blend thoroughly. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut meat in strips about 1/4-inch thick.
Mix all the rest of the ingredients.
Place meat in a glass dish and cover with marinade.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain and dry on paper towels. Spray oven racks with Pam.
Place meat on open oven racks at 150° to 200° and bake for 4 to 8 hours.
Jerky will be brown and will crack when bent when jerky is done.
(Jerky should not break when bent.)
Store in airtight container or freeze.

title: easy stuffed cabbage
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook the quick barley according to instructions on box. When done, rinse and drain. Cut up head of cabbage into pieces. Place in a large cooking vessel and boil for 5 to 7 minutes. Drain cabbage after cooked. In a large bowl, mix cooked cabbage and barley, ground meat, diced onion, salt and pepper. After mixed, pour into the 9 x 13 baking dish. In a bowl, mix the tomato soup with 1/2 can of water and 1/2 can of milk. Pour this over the cabbage mixture in the 9 x 13 dish (if any mixture is left, it can be added while baking because some of the liquid will evaporate during the baking process). Cover with foil. Bake for approximately 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Let set 5 minutes before serving.

title: jerry's cake
directions: Place ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Beat with mixer for 5 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Boil milk, sugar and oleo 7 minutes (rolling boil).
Add peanut butter and chips; stir and add nuts and vanilla.
This is very good, easy and makes a big batch.

title: r.u. peking? chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chicken) in a saucepan; bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
If using wings, cut
off and discard tips and separate wings at joints.
If using drumsticks, cut or snip at bottom and push meat up to form a "drumette" with handle (if desired).
Place chicken in a glass or ceramic bowl; pour seasoning mixture over chicken and mix well to coat. Marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Drain and save marinade.

title: erin's favorite spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook noodles until done in boiling water, then drain.
While noodles are cooking, brown hamburger and onion until brown.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Layer noodles in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place hamburger spaghetti sauce mixture on noodles.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Cook sausage slowly in frypan until no longer pink, crumbling meat while cooking.
In drippings, saute celery and onion until soft but not brown.
Drain excess grease.
In large bowl, put bread cubes.
Add sausage, celery and onion.
Mix lightly.
Add hot broth carefully, being careful not to add too much.
Stuffing should be moist, not soggy!
Add salt, pepper, parsley, beaten eggs and melted butter.
Toss lightly!
Use inside turkey or bake in a buttered casserole.

title: parmesan crab cakes
directions: Mix together first six ingredients until well blended.
Shape mixture into eight 3-inch patties.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook patties 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
For each sandwich, spread two bread slices with tartar sauce.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook the potatoes, carrots, onion and celery together.
While this is cooking, cook the ground beef until it looks gray, then put in the vegetables that are cooking, then add the beans and corn.
Cook until well done.
Season as you wish.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar. Stir until blended. Add 1 1/2 cups nuts. Stir/cook until pulls away from sides of pan.
Add cream of tartar. Stir vigorously. Cook until pinkish tan color.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet. Sprinkle chocolate. Spread when melted. Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on top.

title: coconut chews(cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix powdered sugar and shortening.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press in ungreased, oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake until golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: new orleans bread pudding
directions: Tear up bread and soak in milk until soft.
Add eggs and sugar and turn lightly with hands.
Butter a baking dish and add a dash of vanilla and liquor.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: overnight buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add oleo, sugar, salt, beaten egg and potato flakes. Add flour. Mix at 4 p.m. in the afternoon. Knead down after it rises high at 9 p.m.
Make in buns. Put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Let rise until morning. Put plastic bag over buns while rising. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti angelica(main dish)
directions: Cook spaghetti per directions on box.
Cube cheese and grate in blender.
Add liquid drained from mushrooms and cottage cheese to grated cheese in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in mushrooms, butter salt, black pepper, parsley and nutmeg to taste.
Do not blend.
Add sauce to cooked spaghetti.
Toss until coated.
Serve immediately.

title: dolly's uncooked mints
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Add more powdered sugar as needed to make a stiff dough.
It takes about 1/2 box of sugar. Roll out on board to desired thickness.
Cut with small mint cutters.
Let stand on wax paper uncovered overnight.
Place in container.
It will freeze well.
Yields: 60 mints.
You can buy oil of peppermint at drug store.

title: old timer fruitcake
directions: Mix eggs, molasses, milk and spices together.
In a pan of self-rising flour, work in shortening, then add combined ingredients.
Roll out thin and cut with pie pan.
Makes 14 to 16 layers.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: devilish chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet large enough to hold all the chicken breasts and brown chicken on high on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat, cover and cook for about 10 minutes until done inside.
Add a little white wine, if necessary, to keep from sticking.
Remove chicken breasts from skillet and keep warm.
Add a little more oil to the skillet and saute onion and garlic until onion is soft and transparent.
Add wine and cook until wine is slightly reduced.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Blend cornstarch/flour with 2 tablespoons of chicken broth and blend into sauce.
Blend in mustard and capers.
Spoon sauce over chicken breasts and sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: cherry cinnamon cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling into an 8-inch round layer pan.
Heat at 400° for 15 minutes.
Separate cinnamon rolls and dip edges in butter, then in pecans.
Arrange, topping side up, on top of hot pie filling.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown. Combine lemon peel and icing; spread on rolls.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients
well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
While hot, spread with the crushed pineapple and sweetened juice.

title: caramel icing
directions: Cook all ingredients except marshmallows and vanilla until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows and vanilla.
Beat.

title: layered pudding dessert
directions: Mix oleo, flour, sugar and chopped walnuts.
Spread in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Set aside to cool.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip, then spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding with milk and spread over cheese mixture.
Top with large container Cool Whip after pudding mixture sets up firm.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Bake crusts 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cook onion in boiling water for 5 minutes, drain and arrange on bottoms of pie crusts. Arrange tomatoes on top of onion.
Sprinkle with chive, basil, sugar, salt and pepper.
Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, and cheese.
Spread over top and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix all together.
Pour little barbecue sauce at a time until everything is mixed good.
Put in a pan and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 375°, then turn oven off.
Take meat loaf out of oven.
Pour rest of barbecue sauce on meat loaf and put back in oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: budget salisbury steak with noodles
directions: *May use 1/2 can of each if less gravy is wanted.

title: country fried okra
directions: Cut stems off okra.
In hot skillet, add drippings.
Add okra and stir-fry until tender.
Add garlic salt and black pepper to taste.

title: beer cheese dip
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Add cubed cheese and melt it. Add tabasco, salt, pepper, and garlic. Then add beer for consistency.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Brush with half the butter; sprinkle with 1/2 the cinnamon, sugar mixture.
Roll up.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in a greased muffin tin.
Repeat with other half.
Cover and let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: no-cook fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together in a large bowl.
Add nuts.
In large heavy pan, melt cheese.
Add butter.
When fully melted, pour into sugar and cocoa mixture.
Add vanilla and mix well. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
The mixture will be thick (pat into pan).
Chill, slice and serve.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk
directions: Mix 1 Tbsp. lemon juice or vinegar with 1 cup of sweet milk. Let set for few minutes. Use in place of store bought buttermilk.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Drain and dice chicken, reserving the broth.
Combine the chicken, broth, soup, celery, onion, pecans, salt, pepper, lemon juice, mayonnaise and eggs.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with potato chips. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Whisk together lemon juice and olive oil.
Add olives, bell pepper, scallions, salt and pepper.
Assemble room temperature broccoli back into a round shape in serving bowl.
Pour dressing over the top.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Prepare pie filling as directed, but use only 2 cups of water. Cover surface of pie filling with plastic wrap and cool in pan that you cooked it in.

title: candy buckeyes
directions: Soften margarine to room temperature.
Add sugar, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well; roll into small balls and chill.
Melt wax in double boiler and add chocolate chips.
Use toothpick and roll balls in chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper; cool.
Makes 3 dozen buckeyes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Put 1 cup of the
pecans
into the cheese ball and roll the cheese ball in the
other cup of pecans.
Serve this on Hi Ho crackers or any kind of crackers.

title: no cook pickle slices
directions: Sprinkle first 3 ingredients with salt and celery seed.
Mix sugar and vinegar and pour over pickle mixture.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
These pickles will keep indefinitely, but they are so good, they won't be around for long.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions for sheet cake.
When done, poke holes into cake with knife.
Mix condensed milk with cream of coconut. Spread over hot cake.
Spoon crushed pineapple with juice over cake.
Spread whipped topping over pineapple. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Best when made the day before.
Keep refrigerated.

title: grandma's one-bowl applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl. Cut in butter.
Add molasses, egg and apple sauce. Beat well.
Stir in raisins.
Bake in a greased, floured 8 inch square pan at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or glaze.

title: quick zucchini spaghetti
directions: Shred zucchini using a box grater. Heat a large skillet over moderate heat. Add olive oil to the pan, then add the garlic. When the garlic sizzles, add shredded zucchini. Season zucchini with salt and pepper. Saute shredded zucchini 7 to 10 minutes. Add hot, drained pasta to the pan. Toss spaghetti with zucchini and garlic oil. Add a couple of handfuls of grated cheese to the pan.

title: apple harvest squares
directions: In a bowl combine flour, salt and 1/3 cup sugar.
Cut in butter until the mixture resembles fine crumbs; press into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Arrange the apple slices on top of crumbs; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar with cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine remaining sugar with the rest of the ingredients.
Spoon over baked apples.
Bake for another 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: dump cake
directions: *Can also substitute white or spice cake mix or your choice.

title: quick cake cheesecake
directions: Mix margarine and crumbs.
Put in bottom of 7 x 11-inch pan. In blender, put in hot water and gelatin.
Process at low speed until smooth.
Add cheese one cup at a time.
Process until smooth.
Pour in large bowl of mixer.
Add Cool Whip and mix until smooth (low speed).
Pour over graham crust.
Chill until set (about 1 hour).
Top with filling.
Ready in 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hummus (garbanzo bean dip)
directions: Place drained garbanzos, tahini, lemon juice, crushed garlic and salt in food processor.
Add water and puree, adding more water if necessary to keep mixture from becoming stiff.
Serve with pieces of pita bread.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of brown sugar on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon glaze
directions: Mix sugar and lemon juice until well mixed.

title: party pea casserole
directions: Saute finely chopped celery, onion and green pepper in melted butter.
Remove and mix with remaining ingredients (except onion rings).
Pour all ingredients into greased baking dish. Top with onion rings. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: penne with vodka and tomato cream sauce
directions: Melt butter with oil in heavy large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and saute until translucent, about 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook until almost no liquid remains in pan, stirring frequently, about 25 minutes.
Add cream, vodka and dried red pepper and boil until thickened to sauce consistency, about 2 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
(Sauce can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.)

title: apple rolls
directions: Add packages of Splenda sweetener until sweet.	Core, peel and slice apples.
Wrap apple slices in crescent rolls.
Roll from large end first.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt sugar and butter in pan.
Add Mountain Dew and cinnamon.
Pour over apples.	Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: ellen's chocolate cake
directions: Sift together the sugar and flour.
Put in pan and bring to rapid boil the cocoa, shortening, water and butter or margarine. Add to dry ingredients.
Combine soda, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and add to flour and cocoa mixture. Pour into greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: heavenly hash brownies
directions: Melt 1/4 pound margarine and 2 squares of baking chocolate; cool.
Beat 2 eggs with 1 cup sugar; add to melted chocolate and margarine.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch greased pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: plain pumpkin bread
directions: Put first seven ingredients in large mixing bowl. Make hole in center and add next 4 ingredients.
Mix well and add 1 cup nuts. Pour into 2 to 3 loaf pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple fudge
directions: Mix sugars, cream, pineapple and salt; cook to firm ball stage; add margarine just before removing from heat.
Cut marshmallows into pieces and add to hot mixture.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Add lemon juice and nuts.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken italiano
directions: Bake at 350°.
When almost done, top chicken with Romano or Mozzarella cheese.

title: baked potato topper
directions: Heat together and pour over potatoes.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs and vanilla; beating well.
Combine oats, flour and chocolate morsels.
Mix with butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Drop dough onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes, or until brown. Yields 6 dozen.

title: alef-bet pretzels
directions: In a bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add flour, sugar and salt, and work into a dough.
Cover with a towel and let rise 1 hour.

title: funeral sheet cake
directions: Heat margarine, cocoa and milk to boiling point.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat with mixer until smooth.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° in 3 loaf pans for 1 hour or you can bake in tube pans.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onions and beef in oil.
Add salt, chili powder, Worcestershire and tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans and heat through.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Prepare cornbread and spread evenly over top of casserole.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes until brown.

title: swiss corn bake
directions: Cook fresh corn in 1 cup boiling salted for 2 to 3 minutes, or until just tender; drain well.
If using corn from cob, drain well. If using frozen corn, cook and drain.
If using canned corn, drain well.
Combine corn, evaporated milk, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Turn into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs with the butter or margarine and the remaining 1/4 cup cheese; sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with green pepper rings.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pretty jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water in blender on low.
Add eggs, one at a time (mix on high).
Pour into sherbet dishes.
Let set in refrigerator at least 5 minutes.

title: karo nut pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs; mix with sugar, syrup, melted butter and vanilla and add pecans.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Start at 400° for a few minutes (10).
Turn down to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chops with onions
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops to taste.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Mix onion soup according to directions on can.
Pour evenly over pork chops.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg and water.
Roll chicken in egg mixture then flavored bread crumbs.
Brown in shortening or margarine.
Pour off fat. Mix tomato soup, water, onion, basil, garlic powder and oregano. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: old fashioned peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in microwave on High for 45 seconds. Stir in sugar, milk and syrup. Cook on High 3 minutes; stir well. Cook on High 2 minutes; stir well. Cook on High 1 minute; stir well. Cook on High 1 minute. (Check for soft ball in water; if not solid, cook in increments of 1 minute, stirring between each one. Stir in peanut butter and mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 dish. Cool before slicing.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Place beef in roaster or baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours. Remove meat; discard fat and gristle and break meat into shreds. Return to sauce and bake, uncovered, about 1 more hour, until sauce is of desired consistency.

title: christmas kabobs
directions: You will need 6 toothpicks.

title: mustard custard
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Beat eggs in top part of double boiler.
Beat in sugar.
Add vinegar and mustard mixture. Cook over hot water for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir until cool.
Pour over cream cheese block or use on cold cuts.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator. Can make in microwave.

title: waverly cracker bars
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with Waverly crackers.
By hand, put 2 to 3 pieces of each slivered almonds and chopped pecans on each cracker.
Mix butter and sugar together.
Boil until almost a boil.
Do not overboil, then put by spoonfuls on each cracker. (Do not pour over crackers.) Bake at 325° to 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Take out of pan and put each cracker on aluminum foil. Cool, then put in Tupperware container and seal.
Very good!

title: cottage cheese spring salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix gently.

title: stuffed green peppers and spanish rice
directions: Parboil green peppers; remove and keep water.
Mix together ground sirloin, 1/2 cup rice (uncooked), egg, salt and pepper. Stuff in peppers.
While stuffing peppers, have cooking in the water the following:
onion, carrot, tomatoes, salt, pepper and paprika.
After this has been cooking about 15 minutes, add peppers.
Cover with water if needed and cook 40 minutes.
Add the remaining 1 cup rice and cook 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend
cream
cheese and margarine
until
smooth.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add flavoring.
Blend in eggs,
one
at a time. Add flour and blend well. Bake in
greased
and floured tube pan for 2 hours at 350°.

title: meringue teasers
directions: Beat egg whites in a bowl until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar until stiff peaks form.
Add vanilla and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons into foil covered cookie sheets.
Place in 350° oven, then turn the oven off.
Do not open oven for at least six hours or overnight.

title: layered finger jello
directions: Mix together until dissolved and pour into cake pan to set.

title: brownie cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 2/3 cup margarine.
In large mixer bowl, beat melted margarine, sugar, flour, cocoa, eggs, milk, 2 teaspoons vanilla and baking powder until well blended.
Stir in nuts, if desired.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: turkey sausage quiche
directions: Immerse broccoli in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Cook turkey sausage and garlic until brown; drain on paper towel.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add broccoli, turkey sausage, cheese, bread cubes and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 4 servings. One-thousand calorie recipe.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and dice fruits.
Combine all ingredients and mix gently but thoroughly.

title: spinach balls
directions: Beat eggs well.
Combine stuffing, onion, cheese and seasonings.
Mix together eggs, spinach and stuffing mixture.
Pour melted butter over it.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: spiced peanuts(yields approximately 170 two-ounce cups)
directions: Boil the sugar, water and spices until syrup reaches 293°. Drop peanuts into syrup; stir until nuts look dry.
Spread on waxed paper and let cool and dry.
Fill 1 or 2-ounce cups.

title: green beans and mushrooms
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in covered saucepan for 2 hours.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Beat dry cake mix, butter and 1 egg in large bowl at low speed until crumbly. Press lightly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons vanilla and cream cheese until smooth and fluffy. Spread over crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until set.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Add peanut butter chips.
Shape in 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork tines.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.

title: spring rolls
directions: Cook ground pork; add butter, garlic, vegetables and soy sauce to taste.
Cool.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons on egg roll wrapper. Wrap according to directions.
Deep fry.
Serve wrapped in lettuce leaf and dip in sauce.

title: pear pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into unbaked pie crust.
Cover with another pie crust.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes; reduce to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana "pops"(kids cooking)
directions: Will need 6 short, thick straws (or popsicle sticks).

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to boiling in a 2-quart pan.
Stir in flour, vigorously stirring over low heat until mixture forms a soft ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Drop dough by 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Shape each into finger 4 1/2 inches long and 1 1/2 inches wide with spatula.
Bake until puffed and golden, 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a greased, floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauteed zucchini
directions: Cook bacon over medium heat until crispy; drain on paper towels.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Slice zucchini; add to hot fat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring often, until soft, but not mushy.
Add tomatoes.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Serve with bacon crumbled over top.
Serves 4.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix together flour, salt, cream of tartar and soft drink mix. Add the oil and boiling water.
Stir quickly.
Let cool and mix with hands.
Store in air-tight container.

title: james beard's chinese chews
directions: Mix until crumbly and spread in greased 8 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all items together and chill.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together; mix flour, soda and salt together.
Add to first mixture.
Roll into small balls and place in small muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place a Reese's cup in the center of each cookie. Let cool completely before removing from pan.
(Let cookies be a light golden brown before removing from oven.)

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix well; spread over chocolate chips.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Cook the raw cranberries and 1 cup water until cooked down, about 25 minutes.
Add the sugar, then put through a food mill. Mix the jello in 2 cups boiling water, with 1 cup cold water added.
Stir mixture into cranberry mixture.
Takes awhile to thicken.

title: big o's meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 9 ingredients. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Press into an ungreased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Drain. Drizzle with ketchup. Bake 10 minutes longer. Makes 6 large servings.

title: oriental meat balls
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, onions, mustard, salt, pepper, egg and milk.
Shape into balls and brown in oil.
For sauce, mix remaining ingredients together.
Cook and stir until thickened. Add to meatballs and cook 30 minutes.
(Freezable at this stage.) Add one medium green pepper (cut in strips), large can of pineapple chunks, and cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit 'n yogurt pie(slightly sweet, slightly tangy)
directions: Thoroughly combine mashed fruit and yogurt in a bowl.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust and freeze about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.
Solidly frozen pie may require more time in refrigerator for softer texture.
Store any leftover pie in the freezer.
Other fruits may be used with yogurt of same flavor.

title: keftathes(greek meatballs)
directions: Combine ingredients; mix
well.
Form
into
balls
the size of a golf ball and roll in flour.
Fry in oil until done.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add milk, beaten eggs, melted fat. Mix well; pour into greased pan.
Bake 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: amaretto salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water by cooking over low heat.
Chop up 2 cups pie filling.
Stir in gelatin mixture, sugar, lemon juice, salt and almond extract.
Refrigerate until slightly set. Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate until set.

title: easy prune or plum cake
directions: Measure flour and mix with salt and spices, then add the next 4 ingredients.
Mix together thoroughly with mixer, then fold in nuts.
Pour in well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Place in oven on rack about 5 inches from bottom of oven.
Start in cold oven; bake about 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Allow cake to cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Sift
flour, cut butter into flour.
Stir n sour cream. Drop by	spoon onto baking sheet or place in small muffin tin pan. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oven-fried zucchini spears
directions: Cut zucchini into halves, then crosswise to get finger lengths.
On wax paper, mix all seasonings.
In small bowl, mix oil and water.
Toss zucchini spears in water mixture, then in crumbs.
Arrange on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 475° oven for 7 minutes until brown.
Turn over and bake 3 minutes more.

title: boston clam chowder
directions: Render fat.
Add peppers and onions; saute until translucent. Sprinkle flour over top, stirring.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Add clam broth, gradually bringing to a simmer.
Add potatoes and clams. Continue simmering until potatoes are tender.

title: anise candy
directions: Mix the ingredients in large saucepan.
Stir to just dissolve. Cook to hard crack stage over medium heat (300°) for 25 to 30 minutes from start to boiling.
Do not stir.
After boiling has ceased, add 1 teaspoon anise oil and 1 teaspoon red food coloring. Butter 2 pie plates.
Pour into pie plates.
While still warm, gently make indentations until it cools and holds its shape.
I use the back of a butter knife to make squares.
Don't break through the film.

title: quick and easy bread and butter pickles
directions: Put in kettle the cukes and onions and cover with salt.
Let stand in fridge for 3 to 4 hours.
Rinse well.
Mix together and pour over cukes and onions the turmeric, cloves, mustard seed, celery seed and vinegar.
Bring to a scald.
Do not boil!
Put in jars and seal.

title: venison swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into meat and cut into serving size pieces. Brown meat in margarine, put in small roaster, cover with onions, celery, salt, pepper, and garlic powder. Cover all this with tomato juice and bake covered in oven at 350 degrees for about 2 hours. Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Spread into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Cut into squares.
You can double or triple recipe, but it's easier to mix one pan at a time.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in mixer, butter, brown sugar, sugar, eggs, peanut butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir in by hand oats, chocolate chips, nuts and flour.
Add M&M's to top of cookies.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Cream together (using an electric mixer) the shortening, sugar, eggs and molasses in a large bowl. In a separate large bowl, combine the flour, salt, baking soda, ginger and cinnamon. Prepare the strong coffee in another container (such as a large cup with a pouring lip). Once the initial ingredients are creamed together, alternately add the dry mixture and the strong coffee until all ingredients have been combined.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Cook noodles; rinse in cold water. Layer in 5-quart crock-pot the hamburger, noodles, sauce, pepperoni and cheese. Repeat layers.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 5 hours.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Melt the oleo in a 9 x 14-inch Pyrex in oven.
Mix the milk, baking powder, salt, flour and sugar. Pour mixture over melted butter.
Add any kind of fruit on top of mixture.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, cheese, sour cream and 1/2 cup margarine. Salt and pepper.
Press into pan.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup margarine and corn flakes; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together real good.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Then put the pecans in the bottom of pie shell.
Add chocolate chips on top of pecans.
Pour the filling on top of pecans and let sit for 5 minutes or until pecans have come to the top.
Place in oven for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
You can keep this filling in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.
Be sure to mix well before using again.

title: sauce for fish
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour over a pound of fresh or frozen fish.
Bake at 375° about 1/2 hour.
Serves 2 or 3.

title: home fried yams
directions: Slice yams 1-inch thick.
Combine water and salt; soak yam slices for 20 minutes.
Remove from water; pat dry.
Melt butter in large frypan until bubbly.
Add yams; brown both sides.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with lid; reduce heat to low; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream the peanut butter and oleo together with a mixer.
Add box of sugar; mix well.
Shape into marble size balls and place a toothpick in each when you are ready to dip them into the chocolate coating.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together the sugar, oil, eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Add to first mixture.
Add walnuts.
Pour in 2 greased bread tins. Bake at 360° for 1 hour.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips, chocolate and nuts.
Shape into balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet in a 375° oven for 16 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: fruit cake
directions: Chop nuts and fruit.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, then flour.
Put nuts and fruit in.
Mix well and pour in greased tube pan.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.
Dredge fruits with 1/2 cup of the flour.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Split rolls and remove tops.
Spread individually with finely chopped ham.
Top with cheese.
Replace tops on covered bottoms. Melt margarine.
Add other ingredients.
Pour over rolls in aluminum pans.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 22 minutes.
Rolls may be prepared a day ahead and kept in the refrigerator until needed.
Serves 24.

title: candy nuts
directions: Cook to soft ball stage the sugar, orange juice concentrate and water.
Remove from heat.
Heat the orange peel, nutmeg and walnuts; stir until cloudy and hard.
Dump onto wax paper and separate.

title: decorating icing
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt; beat until fluffy.
Add sugar and water.
Beat well.

title: gingerbread house frosting
directions: Beat together all ingredients for 10 minutes.
Spreads good.

title: black walnut pound cake(this recipe is 125 years old)
directions: Cream
butter
and shortening.	Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Add flavorings.	Mix 1/4 cup flour with nuts and set aside.
Add the
remaining	2
3/4	cups flour alternately with milk.
Fold in nuts
with spoon.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour
and
minutes
in
a 325° oven.
Cool 5 minutes in pan.
Turn out and cool.

title: mango ice cream supreme
directions: Mix chopped mango and crumbled oatmeal cookies with ice cream and blend together.
May
be
frozen
to
serve
later. Serves 2 to 3.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix in a large Dutch Oven or large sauce pan and cook on medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside.
Make pudding with milk; stir in Cool Whip.
Mix the cream cheese mixture with pudding mixture.
Layer crumbs and pudding mixture in an 8-inch plastic flowerpot.
Plant a bouquet of plastic flowers in "dirt" and use a trowel to serve.

title: 7-layer cookie bar
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan, place ingredients as listed. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: spiced mixed olives
directions: Drain liquid from ripe olives and discard.
Drain liquid from stuffed olives and reserve.
Arrange both kinds of olives in a very clean jar.
To reserved stuffed olive juice add garlic, bay leaf, mustard seed, thyme, salt and pepper.
Then use to fill jar adding water to cover if necessary.
Refrigerate until needed and after opening.
Makes 1 pint.

title: uncle frank's delicious oatmeal bread
directions: In mixer bowl, put oats and boiling water; let sit for 1/2 hour.
While it's still cooling, add butter, salt and honey.
When the mixture is almost lukewarm, add yeast to 1/3 cup lukewarm water (110°).
Allow dry yeast to soften for a couple of minutes before adding to oat mixture.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, then knead for 10 minutes.
Put dough in a greased bowl and turn dough to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal soft cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, applesauce and cinnamon together. Sift the flour, soda and salt together.
Add oatmeal, then mix with butter mixture.
Stir in raisins and add nuts.
Drop teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Boil onion and squash together until done; drain and season with butter, salt and pepper.
Mash.
Add cracker crumbs, 1/2 of the cheese, milk and egg.
Stir.
Pour into baking dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in oleo (use a large skillet) until vegetables are tender (about 5 minutes).
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in water and 57 sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Add tomatoes and meat of your choice, ham, cooked chicken or shrimp.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: hot curried fruit bake
directions: Melt butter and pour over well drained fruit.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and curry powder.
Put over fruit and toss lightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 easily.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Form into a ball.
Chill 1 hour or more. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Place poultry in an ovenproof pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook in 400° oven 1 hour or until done.

title: apple crumb pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Stir into apples.
Turn into pie shell.
Combine remaining flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt butter; remove from heat.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, stir until combined.
Stir dry ingredients and walnuts into sugar mixture.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm. Makes 48 bars.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Beat 10 to 15 minutes until fluffy.
Put on cake.
Warm Pillsbury fudge frosting 1 minute, pour over filling.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
